(6, 25, 'WoodyB Power', '+27714111414', 'Mike Clark', 'Not Applicable', '1', 'PO Box 70311', 'Bryanston', 'Gauteng', '2196', 'mike@woodybpower.biz', 'Champagne Valley Power', 'PREAMBLE\r\n* The Champagne Valley in the Central Drakensberg is situated about 30km from Winterton and is entered via the R600 road where it intersects with the P10-1.\r\n* The core area is presently served by a 5MW capacity Eskom substation situated at the intersection of the R600 and the D160, close to the Champagne Sports Resort.\r\n* Development in the Valley has been severely curtailed due to insufficient power capacity, with Eskom being unable to increase their supply. All major hotel, timeshare and private developments are unable to grow their operations.\r\n\r\nPROPOSAL\r\n* We are proposing a 10MW biomass fed power generation facility for the Valley. The supply will be structured according to a distributed energy format, split into separate entities and sited near major users of thermal energy eg the Hotel/Timeshare developments.\r\n* We will purchase the existing electrical reticulation from Eskom, take over the maintenance and enter offtake agreements with local enterprises and residents.\r\n* We will negotiate a PPA with Eskom to supply any surplus energy to the grid.\r\n\r\nSCOPE\r\n* A 10MW gasification installation will require 80,000Tpa biomass to sustain baseload operations at a 90% load factor.\r\n* This feedstock will be sourced from plantation waste left by the major timber growers in the area, Sappi and Masonite, as well as utilising agriwaste left by farmers, within a 30km radius. At present this waste is left infield, presenting a serious fire hazard during the winter months.\r\n* As an area of natural beauty the program underway to eradicate alien species is ongoing and will present another source of feedstock. \r\n\r\nCONCLUSION\r\n* This project will ensure that availability, reliability and quality of power is secured for the Champagne Valley area.\r\n* Local, sustainable jobs will be created throughout the value chain - feedstock processing, generation, maintenance and support.\r\n* Environmentally compliant operation will ensure a minimal environmental impact in an area of significant natural beauty.\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Cogeneration', 'CogenerationReciprocating', 'BiomassCurrent', 'Gas', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '10', '1', '10', '90', '1.05', '.075', '', '85', '', '', 'Quater3', '2015', '', '12', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '220', '10', '1050', '', '.075', 'yes', '', 'commitQ2-2014-Phased', '', '2', '12', 'WoodyB Power', 'Carbo Consulting and Engineering', 'Not Applicable', 'Not Applicable', '4 MW biomass project RSSC Swaziland presently underway', '70000000', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 40, '*Mangweni Local Community will be associated with the project from an early stage. The community land adjoins the Champagne Valley area and most of the employees in the area are drawn from the community. \r\n*The power project is expected to provide up to 20 sustainable jobs per MW installed capacity, ranging from unskilled through to management.\r\n*Gasifier units can be installed on community land eg at schools, clinics or municipal offices to provide thermal as well as electrical power.', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', '2', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '3', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '3', '', 'draft', 'yes', '* 12000 ha commercial timber is planted within a 30km radius of the proposed gasifier site, this will provide 50% of the required feedstock from plantation waste left after harvesting operations, a figure of around 50,000T pa                                                                        * 25000ha maize, soya, kenaf are planted annually within the 30km radius. Around 2T per ha agriwaste is produced from these operations,  ie about 50,000Tpa feedstock                 * 3000ha wattle jungle in the area available for feedstock, about 20,000Tpa for                   * alien species eradication program underway in the area, around 5,000 Tpa ', 'Winterton/Loskop ', '29', '28', '19', '28', '59', '42', 'no', '', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'Generation licence   6 months', '0', '29', '28', '19', '28', '59', '42', 'Cathkin Sub    Intersection of D160 and R600 Champagne Valley', 'no', '', '', '', 'Not Applicable', 'Not Applicable', '* Application will be made to takeover local distribution line from Eskom. ', '18', 'Not Applicable', '0-30', '160', '72.73', '*Gasifier units manufactured in S Africa    * All steel structures sourced locally                  *Feedstock processing equipment', '200', '*Timber handling equipment   * Training centre set up to create pool of employees for biomass power station operation and management skills', '2013-06-20', '2013-07-06', 'true'),
