(19, 95, 'NamPower', '+264 61 205 249', 'Gerson Rukata', 'NamPower Center', '15', 'Luther Street', 'PO Box 2864', 'Windhoek', '9000', 'gerson.rukata@nampower.com.na', 'Kudu Gas to Power Project', 'The Kudu Gas to Power Project (the Project) consists of three distinct yet interrelated projects.  They are the:\r\n•	development of the offshore Kudu Gas Field (the Gas Project); \r\n\r\n•	development of the gas fired Kudu Power Station project (the Power Project); and \r\n\r\n•	transmission integration into the Namibian and South African grid (the Transmission Project).\r\n\r\nThis Power Project, is the proposed development, construction and financing of the 800 MW- 1000MW(nominal) methane gas based Combined Cycle Gas Turbine (CCGT) power station. \r\n\r\nMain cost drivers will be the cost of gas, the recovery of the capital cost of the power station, operations and maintenance of the power station and transmission costs.\r\nThe main decision point of the project will be the Final Investment Decision (FID), for all parties to the project, to be taken on 1 July 2014. \r\n\r\nThe Power Project is to be developed through a special purpose company, Kudu Power Company (Proprietary) Limited (KuduPower), in which NamPower intends to hold a significant equity stake. NamPower will buy all output from KuduPower and intend to on-sell a portion to South Africa.\r\n\r\nThe Power Project will be funded through sponsor’s equity and debt funding, sourced from financial markets in the Southern African region and internationally.', 'Other', '', '', '', 'Gas fired Combined Cycle', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1050', '525', '300', '70', '0.80', 'PPI', '5913 kJ/kWh', '', '', '', 'Quater4', '2017', '', '42', 'mid-merit', '', '336', '16.6', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '12544', '15', '800', 'Transmission Tariff (amount to be determined)', 'ZAR PPI', 'no', 'Expected 85% USD, 15% ZAR', 'commitQ3-2013-Phased', '', '6', '42', 'NamPower', 'Not yet finalised', 'Not yet finalised', 'Not yet finalised', 'NamPower has not finalised its partners in this project. NamPower has no experience in similar projects but will join with international power developers experienced in many similar successful projects.  Two power development partners will join the project from October 2013.  These power developers will bring specific expertise and credibility which will assist with the development of the project and the give confidence to financiers.', '2555559000', '2309164000', '1804177000', 'no', '', '', '', '', 10, 'The project will involve substantial community involvement within Namibia', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '6', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', '', 'no', 'Front end engineering and development (FEED) of gas field development is in process.', '27 June 2017', 'Kudu Project Timetable & Milestones', 'Kudu Project Timetable & Milestones', '6', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '6', 'yes', 'finalised', 'yes', 'Resource studies have been completed although lenders may require independent assessment of these.', 'Uubvlei, Oranjemund, Namibia', '16', '15', '00', '28', '26', '42', 'yes', 'Government of Namibia has agreed that project can use the site.', 'yes', 'yes', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'Generation Licence Application 16 June 2014', '0', '16', '15', '00', '28', '26', '42', 'Kudu Substation', 'no', '24/06/2013', 'no', '', 'NamPower and Eskom have engaged on this project for several years.  Recently meetings have been held with Eskom''s Southern African Energy Business Development Division. The project will require new 400kV and 220kV transmission infrastructure and connections to the Eskom transmission system.  In discussions with Eskom it is clear that the required Kudu related transmission enhancements in South Africa are complimentary in nature and timing with the transmission developments Eskom is already planning for the Northern Cape.  These include the Upington strengthening, the Juno to Aries 400kV line and the Aries SVC.  Joint Power Systems Studies Working Group has been established and should report back by 1 October 2013. ', 'Transmission upgrades required in South Africa have yet to be finalised and are the subject of the Working Group studies.', 'The power station will connect to NamPower''s transmission system in Namibia but will also require additional interconnections to Eskom''s transmission system the design of which will be finalised by the Working Group.', '35', 'Transmission upgrades be required in South Africa have yet to be finalised.  Eskom''s existing supply obligations to Namibia are not firm but are to a maximum of  300MW off-peak and 200MW peak.  Kudu will provide a likely maximum supply of 300MW peak to South Africa and would also offset the current peak purchases from South Africa of 200MW.  It may be that some off-peak exports from South Africa to Namibia continue. ', '0-30', '1254', '10.00', 'There will be many opportunities for South African firms to work on the Kudu project and South African manufacturers should be competitive for much of the plant and equipment required for the project.  The project will use competitive tendering and EPC contracting for all major works.', '1500', 'Even though this is a Namibian project some opportunities may arise in South Africa', '2013-06-24', '2013-07-05', 'true'),
