(34, 53, 'Vedanta Resources plc.', '011 685 3961', 'Mr Marco Nyoni, GM Business Development', 'Vedanta Zinc International', '1', 'Havelock road', 'Aggeneys', 'Aggeneys, Northern Cape', '8893', 'marco.nyoni@vedantajhb.co.za', 'Vedanta Waterberg IPP', '\r\nProject Overview\r\nVedanta Resources plc. (“Vedanta”) is a London listed FTSE 100 diversified resources major with a market capitalisation of over US$4 billion. The Vedanta group has operations in more than eight countries across four continents comprising significant interests in base metals & iron ore mining, oil & gas exploration and production and captive and commercial energy (IPP) production. \r\nVedanta places strong emphasis on partnering with all its stakeholders based on the core values of entrepreneurship, excellence, trust, inclusiveness and growth. The group has operations in India, Zambia, Namibia, South Africa, Ireland, Australia, Sri Lanka and Liberia and a strong organic growth pipeline of projects.\r\nVedanta proposes to construct, commission and operate a 600MW coal-fired Circulating Fluidised Bed Combustors (CFBC) power plant, comprising  two  300MW (“CFBC”) and generator units, radiator air cooled, and associated infrastructure, in the Lephalale Local Municipality, Waterberg District, South Africa.  The proposed Vedanta Waterberg IPP (“VWIPP”) Project is planned to be located entirely within the mining and surface right area of the proposed Dalyshope Phase 1 Coal Mine (“Dalyshope Coal Mine”), owned by Anglo Operations Proprietary Ltd. (“AOL”), a division of Anglo American plc.  Anglo American Thermal Coal (“AATC”) will develop and operate Dalyshope Coal Mine and will supply coal to the VWIPP power station. Vedanta and AATC have signed a Memorandum of Understanding (“MoU”) in this regards and negotiations on a Fuel Supply Agreement (“FSA”) are underway. \r\nThe VWIPP Project will combust a blended coal stream utilising both low-grade coal and Run of Mine (“ROM”) coal from the proposed Dalyshope Coal Mine, currently in its feasibility development phase, for the generation of electricity. Electricity generated will be supplied into the National grid for off-take as part of the National Base Load Independent Power Producer (IPP) base load programme. \r\nFuel Supply:\r\n•	The burning of the less than 3000 kcal/kg fuel by the proposed power plant serves to support the effective utilization of South Africa Coal reserves in that it allows the unlocking of the coal reserve as the power plant will serve to be the anchor off taker of otherwise waste coal. This in turns allows the further exploitation of the coal to support the larger Eskom power plants in the medium to long term.  \r\n•	FSA is being negotiated with AATC.\r\nSupport of National Power Grid:\r\n•	The generation of power from this low grade waste coal, will aid the national power grids reserve margins, in returning it back up to the international acceptable norms and allowing Eskom to claw back on the percentage planned outages of its fleet.\r\nCost drivers:\r\n•	The combusting of otherwise waste coal, with technology which is flexible, to ensure the effective utilisation of South Africa’s coal reserves.\r\n•	Utilisation of dry cooling technology to minimise the demand on our limited water resources.\r\n•	Combining and sharing of infrastructure between AATC and Vedanta, hence limiting the impact on the environment, optimised and effective utilization of capital funds.\r\n•	Ashing back into the open cast cuttings is envisaged, pending the currently being conducted leaching tests, hence reducing the plant and associated ash storage footprint, reduction in the backfilling requirement and allowing access to the temporary sterilized coal reserves once the plant life cycle has been completed and plant decommissioned.\r\nKey decision point:\r\n•	Conclusion of FSA with AATC\r\n•	Receipt of Record of Decision for integrated ESIA\r\n•	Positive outcome from technical study on ability to ash into open cast cuttings\r\n•	Conclusion of Land Lease Agreement with AATC\r\n•	Conclusion of PPA with Eskom\r\n•	Vedanta Board Approval\r\n', 'Thermal', 'Coal', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '600', '300', '540', '90', '0.75', 'cpi', '90%', '', '', '', 'Quater4', '2018', 'This COD is subject to the Eskom Transmission connection being completed and the securing of 99% confidence level water supply.\r\n1st unit COD , 36 -40 months after EPC appointment\r\n2nd unit COD, 42 - 48 months after EPC appointment', '48', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'yes', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '10000', '25', '2350', 'TBA', 'TBA', 'yes', '', 'commitQ2-2014-Phased', '', '6', '48', 'Vedanta Resources plc.', 'TBA', 'TBA', 'TBA', 'Power Business of Vedanta Group in India\r\nVedanta Resources (‘Vedanta) has been building and managing power plants in India since 1997. As of 31 March 2013, Vedanta’s total power generating capacity was 5,510 MW, of which approximately 5,154 MW was from coal based thermal power plants.\r\nThis 5154 MW coal based thermal power includes several commercial Independent  power plants, namely Sterlite Energy’s 2,400 MW coal-based thermal power plant in Jharsuguda, MALCO’s 100 MW coal based thermal power plant in Mettur Dam, and HZL’s wind power plants in Gujarat, Karnataka and Rajasthan aggregating 2,774 MW. \r\nTalwandi Saboo Power Limited (TSPL), a wholly owned subsidiary of Sterlite Energy, is currently constructing a 1,980 MW coal-based independent thermal power plant at Punjab, the first unit of which is expected to be synchronised in the second quarter of fiscal 2014.\r\nSales of units of power increased from 6,554 million units in fiscal 2012 to 8,888 million units of power in fiscal 2013. The increase in sales drove revenue from Vedanta’s commercial power generation business from $420.9 million in fiscal 2012 to $548.7 million in fiscal 2013.\r\n', '15000000000.00', '14000000000.00', '11400000000.00', 'no', '', '', '', '', 25, 'THE VWIPP Project will be structured with a 10% equity allocated to a BEE Partner, that is yet to be selected. Vedanta is in discussion with several interested parties. \r\n\r\n15% of the equity will be allocated to a staff and community trust comprising communities from either the project are or from Vedanta''s mining operations ("BMM") in Northern Cape Province of South Africa.', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '8', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', 'All authorisations (mining environmental, integrated water use licence and waste) are in the process of being prepared. On 23rd July 2013 Vedanta will be meeting with DEA (Botswana) in Gaborone in connection with any possible cross border environmental issues for the Dalyshope Coal Mine and the VWIPP Project  then further public meetings are planned from 30 July to 1 August 2013 in Lephalale.', 'no', 'The coal mine is in final feasibility stage with the VWIPP Project as an offtaker of coal from the mine, at volumes sufficient to supply a 600MW station.', 'Coal production will be synchronised with the VWIP project as part of the negotiation of the FSA. This is expected to be concluded by the end of Q1 2014.', 'TBA', 'TBA', '8', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '6', 'yes', 'draft', 'no', 'The fuel supplier is AAATC, an operating division of Anglo Operations Limited. They have completed all the relevant resource evaluation studies required to take the mining project to feasibility stage. ', 'Dalyshope 232 LQ , Lephelale, Limpopo', '27', '15', '16.004', '23', '34', '5.258', 'yes', 'Land lease agreement is being negotiated with AATC, and targetted to be completed by end Q1 2014.', 'no', 'yes', '03/02/2014', 'yes', '04/09/2013', '02/06/2014', 'no', '', '', 'ESIA application registered DEA Ref No: 14/12/16/3/3/3/80', '56', '27', '11', '56.64', '23', '32', '33.49', 'Masa substation', 'yes', '01/12/2011', 'yes', 'Ref No: 69240463', 'Transmission and Distribution network connection for the required grid connection.', 'Power supply to be 400Kv to the Masa substation. 756KV bus @ Masa', 'Eskom', '36', 'n/a', '0-30', '3000', '30.00', 'This is yet to be determined.', '1500', 'This is yet to be determined.', '2013-06-26', '2013-07-12', 'true'),
