(37, 154, 'Powerthane', '021-948 7051', 'C. Bellingan', 'Bellingan Engineers', '3', 'Ferguson', 'Stikland Triangle', 'Bellville', '7530', 'bellingn@mweb.co.za', 'Biomass Energy', 'Biomass Energy Generation Project at Hermanus New Harbour, to generate 6MW electricity and 6MW thermal, specifically for Abalone Farms.  Thermal energy applied to heat sea water to ensure Abalone growth, electrical energy for sea water pumps.  Project to have three digesters, to ferment waste material, 100 tons / 24 hrs to methane, with three 2MW methane engine generators coupled to 11 Kv altenators.\r\n\r\nCreate 300 new unskilled jobs to collect all fermentable waste including foreign vegetation, in the Botriver, Hermanus, Stanford and Agulhas Flats area.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2013-06-27', '0000-00-00', ''),
(38, 144, 'COEGA DEVELOPMENT CORPORATIONT', '+27 83 397 5258', 'LUVUYO MKONTWANA', 'COEGA BUSINESS CENTRE', '01', 'CNR ALCYON RD & ZIBUKO ST, ZONE 1', 'COEGA IDZ', 'PORT ELIZABETH', '6100', 'luvuyo.mkontwana@coega.co.za', 'COEGA COMBINED CYCLE GAS TURBINE POWER STATION', 'The Coega IDZ is still clearly the preferred location for the fast tracking of a CCGT Power Station Project for the following reasons:\r\n•There is a 2005 Cabinet resolution to import gas via the Port of Ngqura and to generate 1,600MW at Coega utilising that gas;\r\n•There is a prime site available for the Power Station and further options for other power stations such as the PET Coke power station associated with Project Mthombo;\r\n•There are existing and potential berthing facilities in or adjacent to the Port for the importation of LNG;\r\n•Sea water cooling is readily available in proximity to the CCGT Power Station site;\r\n•The CDC was already undertaking a sea water usage study for various other projects including the power station;\r\n•There is a 400kV electrical transmission corridor available to connect to the national grid through the Dedisa sub-station;\r\n•Potentially help in balancing the national power grid by having generation capacity in the south of the country;\r\n•Reduction in transmission losses to the EC;\r\n•A large amount of preparatory work had already done by CEF/iGas;\r\n•Impetus to the Eastern Cape economy by increasing economic activity and employment creation that would lead to the much needed socio-economic development in the region;\r\n•Attract new industries on the back of power availability;\r\n', 'GasPlant', 'CCGT', 'LNG', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2500', '2500', '2500', '60', '00', 'N/A', 'N/A', '', '', '', 'Quater4', '2016', '', '0', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'yes', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '38000', '25', '0', '-', '-', 'no', '', 'commitQ2-2014-Phased', '', '12', '36', 'Energy Investor (DoE Preferred Bidder) to be located at Coega IDZ', '', 'N/A', 'N/A', '- CCGT Feasibility Study\r\nThe CDC under the guidance of the Department of Energy (DoE) finalised feasibility studies for a 3,200 MW Combined Cycle Gas Turbine at the Coega IDZ. This feasibility study was borne out of the need for electricity generation due to the electricity crisis that the country was experiencing. In 2009, the study conducted by KPMG-led consulting project team resulted in the pre-feasibility study for the Coega CCGT Power Plant. The objective of this Pre-feasibility Study Report was to carry out a preliminary analysis of the suitability and viability (strategic, technical, financial, regulatory, legal and commercial) of a gas fired power station to be located at Coega in the Eastern Cape in South Africa. The feasibility study was accepted by the DoE in July 2009 and it was proposed that a further detailed feasibility study be carried out to include project definition, structure, and implementation plan, roles of stakeholders, technical\r\nconfigurations, regulatory and financial arrangements and legal framework amongst others.\r\n', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 25, 'The impetus of building a CCGT plant to the Eastern Cape economy by increasing economic activity and employment creation that would lead to the much needed socio-economic development in the region;', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '6', 'no', '', '', '', '', '', 'no', 'Dependent on work done in other state owned companies including the CEF''s PETROSA/ iGas, and work done by independent Fuel/Gas related industry players', 'no', '                                                                          #400kV Transmission Line between\r\nCCGT site and Dedisa Substation\r\n(Eskom) RoD\r\n#Coega IDZ Rezoning RoD                                                                                                                          #Coega Marine Pipeline Servitude/ Sea Water Intake Scoping Report           ', 'no', 'CDC, Transnet and NMB Metro have formed a forum that identified a basket of projects for integrated planning and development in the region. The list of projects identified include the development and establishment of an LNG Terminal and CCGT Power Plant at the Port of Ngqura. Though no concrete agreement has been reached yet on the implementation of the LNG Terminal at Port of Ngqura, there has however been very positive developments stemming from the forum discussion around the LNG Project, such as:\r\n\r\n1.	The LNG Berth has now been included in the Port of Ngqura Port Development Framework Plan, this means from a spatial perspective they are making provision for it.\r\n2.	Feasibility Study for an LNG Terminal at the Port of Ngqura that will be undertaken by TNPA (announcement on the 29th May 2013 at EC Ports and Maritime Conference by TNPA CE).\r\n3.	Continuous engagement with TNPA (Business Development and Commercial) on the project to ensure momentum and lend support where required to ensure the realisation of the project in Ngqura.\r\n', '', '', '', '6', 'project', '', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '6', 'no', 'draft', 'no', 'The CDC under the guidance of the Department of Energy (DoE) finalised feasibility studies for a 3,200 MW Combined Cycle Gas Turbine at the Coega IDZ. This feasibility study was borne out of the need for electricity generation due to the electricity crisis that the country was experiencing. In 2009, the study conducted by KPMG-led consulting project team resulted in the pre-feasibility study for the Coega CCGT Power Plant. The objective of this Pre-feasibility Study Report was to carry out a preliminary analysis of the suitability and viability (strategic, technical, financial, regulatory, legal and commercial) of a gas fired power station to be located at Coega in the Eastern Cape in South Africa. The feasibility study was accepted by the DoE in July 2009 and it was proposed that a further detailed feasibility study be carried out to include project definition, structure, and implementation plan, roles of stakeholders, technical configurations, regulatory and financial arrangements and legal framework amongst others.', 'Coega IDZ, Port Elizabeth, Eastern Cape, South Africa', '25', '42', '32.7', '33', '47', '00.4', 'yes', 'The Coega Development Corporation (CDC) (Pty) Ltd is the operator of the Coega Industrial\r\nDevelopment Zone (IDZ).The CDC (registration number 82 / 03891 / 07) is incorporated and\r\nregistered under the Companies Act of South Africa. The CDC is wholly-owned by the South African Government. The CDC was established in 1999 and is the successor in law to the Coega Implementing Authority, the body mandated in 1997 by the South African Government to implement the Coega Industrial Development Zone. The Coega IDZ is South Africa’s premier location for new industrial investments covering 11 000 hectares of land. The Coega IDZ is a phased development around industry clusters with Custom Secure Areas (CSA) dedicated for export oriented manufacturing companies located in the zone. Coega offers a platform for global exports by attracting foreign and local investment in manufacturing industries. A strategic Development Framework Plan (DFP) for the Coega IDZ has been developed focusing on infrastructure development and facilities for the Core Development Area (CDA) comprised of 6,500 hectares.', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', '#Marine Pipeline Servitude/ Sea Water intake Environmental Authorisation (estimated 8 months)                                                                                                                 #LNG -Power CCGT Power Station Environmental Authorisation (estimated 14 months)', '5.5', '25', '40', '37.8', '33', '44', '31', 'Eskom Dedisa SubStation, Coega IDZ', 'no', '', '', '', 'In2006,Eskom was granted an environmental authorisation for the construction of the proposed 400/132 KV substations and the associated Transmission and Distribution infrastructure for the in the Coega IDZ. This includes the construction of the Transmission lines between the Dedisa Substation and the proposed Coega CCGT site location.                                                                                                                        In recent months , Eskom has engaged the Coega Development Corporation on spatial planning and SHEQ elements relating to their planned implementation of the proposed 400 KV transmission, initially between  focussing on the link between the Dedisa Substation and Grassridge Substation. The future planned phase includes the link between Dedisa Substation and Zone 10 of the Coega IDZ, where the Coega CCGT Power Station is planned.', 'The proposed power plant will be located in the NMBM, specifically in the Coega Industrial\r\nDevelopment Zone (IDZ). The power plant will be connected to the Dedisa sub-station, which in turn is connected to the national grid at 400 kV and in future at 765 kV', 'Eskom', '24', 'N/A', '85-100', '11000', '28.95', 'This intervention unlocks the value resulting from the creation of a new industry, with its associated upstream and downstream activities in the distribution and logistics channel and in the internal components supply chain, support and aftercare. This will present opportunities for Small-Medium Micro Enterprises (SMME), and the outlay of SMME development interventions.', '150', 'The benefits to the local economy will penetrate beyond the local skilled jobs and training to include logistics opportunities and additional value chain opportunities, thus creating a new industry in the Eastern Cape. The developmental impacts can be viewed in the context of the enabling infrastructure that unlocks the wind tower manufacturing facility. These are the Coega IDZ and the integrated distribution channel (Ngqura deep-water port, logistics, and freight transport solutions) that links to downstream industry creation for enterprises and service providers. ', '2013-06-27', '2013-07-09', 'true'),
