(41, 177, 'Sappi Southern Africa Limited', '011 407 8472', 'Tyrone Hawkes', 'Sappi', '48', 'Ameshoff Street', 'Braamfontein', 'Johannesburg', '2001', 'tyrone.hawkes@sappi.com', 'Ngodwana - GoCell Turbine', 'Sappi has a strategic intent to develop renewable energy generation facilities produced from biomass sources within the group''s control. This project on a key production site is one of five being submitted in this RFRI. It is Sappi''s intent to develop a portfolio of these projects.\r\n\r\nThe recent conversion (Project GoCell) of Sappi''s Ngodwana mill to produce chemical cellulose and the resultant increase in steam production from the Chemical Recovery process - presents the opportunity to produce at least an extra 15MW of power. This project proposes installing a new 40MW (predominantly condensing) steam turbine. The over-size of the turbine is due to varying steam demands and to maximise power production during plant slowdowns and stoppages.\r\n\r\nThis project has the potential to be commissioned very quickly. It does not require environmental authorisation and has an existing connection to the Eskom grid.\r\n\r\nFuel Supply:- Pulping Liqour (Wood residue from pulping)\r\n\r\nDecision Points:- The project is close to being bid compliant under the REIPP rules with no permits outstanding.  Sappi requires certainty on the IPP termination clauses and tariff escalation provisions within the PPA before progressing to financial close.\r\n\r\nMain cost drivers:- Capital and fuel costs.\r\n\r\nUnusual Features:- High uncertainty on electricity output - will be well defined within the next year.\r\n\r\nAll financial analyses done at ZAR9 to USD. Cresco Project Finance Consulting were used in the development of the financial model supporting the inputs to the submission.', 'Thermal', 'BiomassExpanded', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '40', '40', '18', '77', '0.573', 'Basket of transport and fuel.', '', '', '', '', 'Quater2', '2015', 'Placing orders on turbine would fix the scheduled COD. This may make the COD date sooner than 14 months from signature of PPA.', '14', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'yes', 'STPPP and Export power agreements with Eskom.', 'no', '', '296', '10', '960', '', 'Basket of transport and fuel.', 'yes', '', 'fastQ2-2013-24Month', '', '4', '12', 'Sappi Southern Africa Limited', 'Siemens (to be confirmed)', 'IDC', 'None', 'Sappi has an installed capacity of 803MW of power globally. (Sappi Turbines - 5 Hydros, 2 Gas, 31 Steam, on 14 sites in 7 countries).', '12114000000', '12071000000', '11276000000', 'yes', '', '', '', '', 5, 'None.', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '', 'no', '4', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', '02/12/2013', 'yes', '02/12/2013', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'project', '', 'no', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '', '3', '', 'finalised', 'yes', 'A  bid-compliant financial model has been developed and current assumptions relating to CAPEX and OPEX to be confirmed through signing of legal agreements.  ', 'Ngodwana Mill site, Mpumalanga', '30', '39', '33.95', '25', '34', '38.22', 'yes', 'Sappi owned site.', 'yes', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'Environmental and other authorisations not required for this specific project.  ', '0.270', '30', '39', '33.98', '25', '34', '31.69', 'Sappi Ngodwana/ Eskom - 132 kV Distribution sub station.', 'no', '', '', '', 'Discussions are underway with Eskom to ascertain what is required to utilise our existing main supply agreements. The main supply connection has a notified maximum demand exceeding the requirments of this project.  Sappi has a connection and use of system agreement with Eskom,  which we anticipate would need merely an amendment for this project.', 'Not required as the existing Eskom substation will be utilised.  This substation is fed by three lines from Marathon, Prairie and Machadodorp.', 'Connect to existing Eskom substation at Ngodwana Mill.', '1', 'Not applicable.', '65-75', '199', '67.23', 'Civil, electrical and mechanical installation.', '30', 'Electrical and mechanical equipment (to be assessed)', '2013-06-28', '2013-07-12', 'true'),
(42, 179, 'Newcastle cogeneration (Pty)ltd', '+27842192000', 'Mark Otto', 'Newcogen ', '3', 'Karbochem Road', 'Karbochem', 'Newcastle', '2940', 'mark@iq3.co.za', 'NEWCOGEN 2', 'Supply of 29 MW of power based on a CCGT and gas engine principle for the existing plant in Newcastle.\r\n\r\nMethane Rich gas from SpringLights gas will be utilised under the current gas supply agreement that has a 15 year term agreement.\r\n\r\nNewcogen has a current generation license for 18MW and has a PPA with Eskom under the MTPPP contract for the supply of 13MW of power until March 2015.\r\n\r\nThe plant has existing Siemens tornado turbines each with an output of 5 MW that would be revamped to extend the guarantees . Waste heat from the turbines would be passed through newly constructed HRSG''s and a steam condensing turbine of 10 MW installed to provide the combined cycle.\r\n\r\nThis project is for the reconstruction of the existing facility to convert the plant to CCGT(combined cycle gas turbine) based facility that can be achieved in 16 months from the award of a PPA.\r\n\r\nCOD WOULD BE MARCH 2015\r\n\r\nPHASE 1\r\nThe first phase will be to install 10 MW of containerise engines, increasing the load to 14 MW . This phase would be completed by May 2014.GT 1 would be refurbished in terms of OEM requirements . \r\n\r\nPHASE 2. 5 MW of power could be available from MARCH 2014\r\n\r\nPHASE 3.\r\nRevamp of the CCGT plant to provide an additional 10 MW of power . COD would be March 2015.\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Cogeneration', 'Integrated', 'Recomission', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '29', '10', '28.5', '95', '150', 'CPI OR FUEL COST INDEX', '', '45', '', '', 'Quater1', '2015', 'The project scope will be defined once a PPA is negotiated. thereafter the project critical path will be determined by the sourcing of an additional 132KV transmission line into the Newcastle Municipality main grid as agreed by the Municipality.', '16', 'peaking', '12', '355', '15', 'yes', '', 'yes', 'MTPPP Contract no 4600001872 for 13 MW', 'yes', 'The project requires a reconstruction  of the current  CHP plant currently operating  at Newcastle cogeneration under the Eskom MTPPP . The project will be developed in phases with the installation of gas engines, the servicing of the existing plant and upgrading of the steam turbine to provide a facility capable of producing 29 MW of power by March 2015', '150', '15', '1200 ', 'BASE DATE FOR TARIFF PROPOSED IS JULY 2013 - ADJUSTED BY CPI OR FUEL COST INDEX FOR THE COD DATE', 'PPI', 'yes', '', 'fastQ2-2013-24Month', '', '2', '16', 'IPSA Plc', 'IPSA Plc with Turbine Efficiency Ltd', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'IPSA Group PLC ("IPSA") was founded in 2005 to develop, own and operate power generation projects in Southern Africa. The first South African plant built by IPSA commenced commercial operations in May 2007. The plant comprises two Siemens Tornado gas turbines each 6 MW , one Siemens steam turbine of 6 MW and two 55 t/h Aalberg boilers (HRSG''s). The plant has a nominal capacity of 19,2 MW and steam production of 110 t/hr .   ', '9140000', '51720000', '58070000', 'yes', '', '', '', '', 25, 'Newcastle cogeneration has established programmes in place in terms of Socio-Economic development...support of the Qhawelesizwe primary school in Newcastle. In terms of Economic development Newcastle has commenced with the development and growth of Jabulany Construction in Newcastle. Both of the initiatives are sanctioned in terms of the legislative requirement and will be extended in terms of the expansion plans of Newcastle Cogeneration. In addition Newcastel Cogeneration has in cooperation with the CHIETA SETA trained junior technicians fro internship purposes and will continue to provide the on the job internship programmes for Technikon diplomats', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '4', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', '31/03/2015', 'yes', '31/03/2015', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '4', 'project', '', 'no', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '', '4', '', 'draft', 'yes', 'Lenders will seek to review the transmission line requirements and connection to the grid in line with the Municipal requirements. The EIA currently in place for Newcastle Cogeneration will require a basic assessment only as the footprint will not exceed the original 1 Ha approved.', 'NEWCASTLE', '29', '93', '30', '27', '74', '64', 'yes', 'Newcastle Cogeneration operates on the existing site under a long term lease with Karbochem. The conversion to the CCGT unit will require no additional land as the existing plant will be modified to suit. The current turbines will be retrofitted. The current boilers will be dismantled and replaced  with more efficient HRSG''s. An existing steam turbine will be replaced with a condensing turbine in the existing steam turbine hall. Discussions with the Newcastle municipality for the routing of the 132KV line are at an advanced stage and servitudes have been identified. The proposed routing  has been approved and the length determined. The Newcastle Municipality have approved the leasing of an adjacent site for the construction of the required substation ', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'Newcastle has an existing generation license for 18 MW. This could be extended.Wheeling agreements are in place. The EIA process concluded for the existing facility has been reviewed and will require formal application. SRK have been appointed to revise the process', '1.5', '29', '97', '63', '27', '77', '85', 'Karbochem', 'no', '', '', '', 'Eskom Executive - DR Lennon, MR.Lakmeeharan.                                                           Akash Prakash -PPA Manager', '132 KV transmission to link with existing municipal transmission line whhich has been agreed to in principle.', 'Newcastle Municipality', '12', 'N/A', '0-30', '75', '50.00', 'Boiler manufacture, steam system upgrade, control system upgrade, transmission line, substation and MCC', '50 ', 'The refurbishment of the existing turbines can create opportunities to train SA based technicians on the turbines as these are currently the only turbines installed in SA . The current project structure will include the development of local skills in project management, instrumentation, mechanical maintenance of turbines and generators, control systems upgrades in line with OEM specifications.', '2013-06-28', '2013-07-12', 'true'),
(43, 180, 'Umbono Capital Partners (Pty) Ltd', '0114845005', 'Ian McCutcheon', '3rd Floor, Old Trafford, Isle of Houghton', '13', 'Boundary Road', 'Houghton', 'Johannesburg', '2198', 'imccutcheon@umbono.co.za', 'Waterberg Coal IPP Project', 'Umbono Capital Partners (Pty) Ltd (“Umbono”) owns the Waterberg Coal Project located 7km west of Lephalale in Limpopo Province, South Africa. \r\n\r\nUmbono is considering developing a Coal-fired Power Plant as an Independent Power Producer ("IPP"). As a concept the intention would be to use the coal resources within its Waterberg Coal Project to fuel the IPP, and to develop the IPP in parallel with the coal project.\r\n\r\nIn order to develop the IPP, Umbono will commence a process of establishing suitable international and local, financial and technical partners to take the project forward.\r\n\r\nUmbono''s IPP project is currently at an early stage of development. Details regarding site location, plant capacity, developmental timelines and financial considerations have not been finalised and will be subject to further study during the development of the IPP concept.\r\n\r\nThe Waterberg Coal Project ("the Project" is currently at Pre-Feasibility Study ("PFS") phase. The Project comprises a new order Prospecting Right for coal over the farms Groothoek 504LQ and Eendracht 505LQ. The two farms comprise an area of 2,048 Ha. \r\nThe Prospecting Right is valid until 31 July 2015.\r\n\r\nThe two farms were originally owned by ISCOR. A total of 81 exploration boreholes have been drilled across the Project. A SAMREC compliant resource of 485 Mt of coal, of which 80% is an Indicated Resource, was reported on the Project by Venmyn Deloitte in March 2013. Mine development options studies were subsequently completed in June 2013. The results of these studies suggest that the Project is well placed to mine the resource at a rate of 12 Mtpa (million tons per annum) and deliver a minimum of 2.5 Mtpa of coal suitable for burning in a coal fired power station. \r\n\r\nDetailed mine design is expected to be completed by December 2013 with a Definitive Feasibility Study expected to be completed in mid-2014. The Mining Right, Water Use Licenses and Environmental Approvals are expected to be approved by the end of 2015. Allowing two to three years for construction, Umbono expects first coal to be mined in 2018.\r\n\r\nA profile of Umbono and the Project will be submitted as part of the final submission to this RFRI. ', 'Thermal', 'Coal', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '750', '250', '600', '81', '0.75', '1% higher than inflation', '', '', '', '', 'Quater4', '2019', '', '48', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '18750', '40', '1000', '', 'Fuel Cost to be linked to the Coal Price Index; and Operating Cost to be linked to SA CPI', 'yes', '', 'commitQ2-2015-Phased', '', '6', '48', 'Umbono Capital Partners (Pty) Ltd ("Umbono")', 'The selection of a technology partner has not been finalised. Suitable partners will be selected from leading local and international industry participants. ', 'Umbono is a black owned South African company. If required, further suitable partners will be selected from leading local industry participants.', 'Suitable partners will be selected from leading international industry participants and funders. ', 'The Waterberg IPP is the first project to be developed by Umbono. However Umbono has more than 5-years of working experience with Eskom delivering on a range of advisory mandates, including assisting Eskom’s Resources & Strategy department in the development of a set of analysis tools to evaluate new build programmes. Umbono has embarked on a strategy to combine our extensive experience in the energy industry with our natural resource assets to develop a leading Southern African energy business. Umbono will partner with a leading energy operator and EPC to facilitate the development of energy assets within the Southern African arena.', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 26, 'Umbono has every intention to advance local economic development within Lephalale, Limpopo and South Africa in general. Umbono is already a participant in the Lephalale Development Forum and has commenced a process of engagement with the Lephalale Municipality in order to determine the local economic development projects that will be suitable in parallel with the development of the coal mine. The development of the IPP will similarly look to develop local economic development.\r\n\r\nUmbono has an established history of community development in South Africa. \r\nIn 2000, Umbono established key broad-based social impact trusts in South Africa. The Inhlakanipho Education and Development Trust (“IEDT”) was founded and established in 2000 by the major shareholders of the Umbono Group to serve as an educational intervention for black South Africans from disadvantaged backgrounds. It currently owns 13% of Umbono, which is also the primary source of its funding. Since inception, the IEDT has made a significant difference in the lives of 31 high school level beneficiaries, and has supported disadvantaged schools in several projects.\r\n\r\nA second Trust, the Umholi Development Trust, was founded and registered in 2007 as part of Umbono''s desire to make a positive social impact in the countries in which it operates. The Umholi Trust currently owns 10% of Umbono Capital in South Africa and utilises dividends to fund Umholi beneficiaries. The Vision of the Umholi Trust is to invest in the next generation of African leaders by making an impact on the lives of students at the university or post-graduate stage. The Umholi Trust seeks to ensure that beneficiaries are prepared for their careers in whatever sphere of society they seek to operate, and are solidly grounded through a good tertiary education and sound Christian principles guided by a Biblical Christian worldview. The Umholi Trust helps beneficiaries to become more effective leaders within their communities and thereby to have a positive impact on South Africa, Africa and ultimately the world. \r\n\r\nEach year Umholi selects deserving beneficiaries to receive the Umholi Scholarship - these being university level candidates demonstrating excellence and leadership potential. This scholarship provides funding for a tailor-made "life experience" together with a year-long mentorship programme. Since 2007 the Umholi Trust has provided its Leadership Scholarship to 33 Beneficiaries.\r\n', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '6', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', 'The Waterberg Coal Project is currently at Pre-Feasibility Study phase.\r\nA SAMREC compliant resource of 485 Mt of coal was reported on the Project by Venmyn Deloitte in March 2013. Mine development options studies were completed in June 2013. The results of these studies suggest that the Project is well placed to mine the resource at a rate of 12Mtpa (million tons per annum) and deliver a minimum of 2.5 Mtpa of coal suitable for burning in a coal fired power station. \r\n\r\nIn terms of the timing of the coal project: detailed mine design as part of the Pre-Feasibility Study is expected to be completed by December 2013 with a Definitive Feasibility Study expected to be completed in mid-2014. The Mining Right, Water Use Licenses and Environmental Approvals are expectd to be approved by the end of 2015. Allowing two to three years for construction, GCMC expects first coal to be mined in 2018. GCMC is in the process of engaging with Transnet, Eskom and the DWA with regard to rail, power and water supply.', 'no', 'The Waterberg Coal Project comprises a new order prospecting right for coal which is valid until 31 July 2015. At this stage no production/mining or environmental authorisations are in place. Applications will be submitted on completion of the Pre-Feqasibility Study in Q1 2014.', 'no', 'The Project is currently at PFS level. Plant construction is expected to commence in 2016.', '2018', 'A high-level schedule will accompany this submission', 'A high-level schedule will accompany this submission', '6', 'project', '', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '6', 'no', 'none', 'no', 'The feasibility study with respect to the Waterberg coal project will be completed in mid-2014.', 'Lephalale, Limpopo, South Africa', '27', '24', '12', '23', '56', '53', 'no', '', 'no', 'no', '', 'yes', '31/12/2014', '31/12/2015', 'no', '', '', 'At this stage no authorisations or government approvals have been submitted or approved for the IPP project. Umbono intends to submit all relevant applications during its feasibility study, in Q4, 2014, in order for approvals to be secured by Q4, 2015. ', '40', '27', '32', '53', '23', '42', '47', 'Lephalale', 'no', '', '', '', 'At this stage no meetings have been held with Eskom regarding the IPP. Umbono has however had a number of engagements with Eskom''s Primary Energy Division regarding the Waterberg Coal Project since 2009. Engagements with Eskom''s Primary Energy Division are now progressing to an advanced stage.', 'Details regarding transmission and grid requirements will be determined during the feasibility study for the IPP.', 'The intention of the IPP is to connect to the Eskom grid.', '48', 'The project is located within South Africa.', '100+', '6000', '40.00', 'This will be determined during the Feasibility Study', '1200', 'This will be determined during the Feasibility Study', '2013-06-28', '2013-07-12', 'true');
