(44, 177, 'Sappi Southern Africa Limited', '011 407 8472', 'Tyrone Hawkes', 'Sappi', '48', 'Ameshoff Street', 'Braamfontein', 'Johannesburg', '2001', 'tyrone.hawkes@sappi.com', 'Ngodwana - Biomass Boiler', 'Sappi has a strategic intent to develop renewable energy generation facilities produced from biomass sources within the group''s control. This project on a key production site is one of five being submitted in this RFRI. It is Sappi''s intent to develop a portfolio of these projects. \r\n\r\nThis project is green with a high load factor. EIA has been approved. Feasibility complete and will utilise existing grid connection point.\r\n\r\nThis project proposes the construction of a new 150 tph Continuous Ash Discharge biomass boiler and a 45MW condensing turbine at Sappi''s Ngodwana Mill.\r\n\r\nFuel Supply:- The source of biomass will be from Sappi''s surrounding forests in the form of forest resedue, as well as, biomass generated on site.\r\n\r\nMain Cost Drivers:- Capital and biomass cost. Although Sappi has control over the sourcing of the biomass,  it has little control over fuel and other related costs (including wages), it therefore requires the tariff escalation within the PPA to be linked to a basket of indices for cost drivers that are outside of Sappi''s control.\r\n\r\nDecision Points:- The project is close to being bid compliant under the REIPP rules with no permits outstanding.  Sappi requires certainty on the IPP termination clauses and tariff escalation provisions within the PPA before progressing to financial close.\r\n\r\nPlease note, all financial analyses done at ZAR 9 to USD. Cresco Project Finance Consulting were used in the development of the financial model supporting the inputs to the submission.', 'Thermal', 'NewBiomass', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '45', '45', '40', '84.4', '0.607', 'Basket relating to cost drivers.', '', '', '', '', 'Quater1', '2016', 'Not applicable', '24', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'yes', 'STPPP and 