(46, 177, 'Sappi Southern Africa Limited', '011 407 8472', 'Tyrone Hawkes', 'Sappi', '48', 'Ameshoff Street', 'Braamfontein', 'Johannesburg', '2001', 'tyrone.hawkes@sappi.com', 'Tugela - Recovery Boiler Retrofit to Biomass', 'Sappi has a strategic intent to develop renewable energy generation facilities produced from biomass sources within the group''s control. This project on a key production site is one of five being submitted in this RFRI. It is Sappi''s intent to develop a portfolio of these projects.\r\nThis project proposes the conversion of one of Tugela Mill''s existing recovery furnace into a biomass boiler - producing 100 tph steam for a 25MW full condensing turbine. An SPV comprising debt and equity partners will be established for the project.\r\n\r\nThis project is green.  It will utilise an existing grid connection to Eskom and be brought online relatively quickly as the boiler already exists and requires a retrofit only. The location is on the North Coast of KZN where current electricity supply is restricted.\r\n\r\nFuel supply:- Forest residue from Sappi''s KZN forests will form the main (guaranteed) source of biomass,  with the option to use other sources of biomass which include: sugar cane trash, bagasse, sawmill and municipal(garden) waste.\r\n\r\nDecision Points:- Sappi requires certainty on the IPP termination clauses and tariff escalation provisions within the PPA before progressing to financial close. A Basic Assessment for atmospheric emission and waste management license would be required.\r\n\r\nMain cost drivers:- Significant rehabilitation is required to make equipment operable. Forest biomass cost.\r\n\r\nPlease note, all financial analyses done at ZAR 9 to USD. Cresco Project Finance Consulting were used in the development of the financial model supporting the inputs to the submission.', 'Thermal', 'NewBiomass', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '25', '25', '22', '81.5', '0.944', 'Basket relating to cost drivers', '', '', '', '',