(71, 221, 'Gert Linde', '0823211422', 'Gert Linde', 'In The Jungle', '8 ', 'Bergzicht road', 'Somerset West', 'Somerset West', '7130', 'gert@envirorisk.co.za', 'DYSSELSDORP RE-POWER', 'Dysselsdorp Re-Power (Pty) Ltd is the project company for the 75MW Solar Energy Plant.\r\nEnvirorisk Assessment developed the project through phase 1 and 2. The Pre-Bid and Bidding phase was handed to Pegasus Energy Development to complete the process for the 3rd bid. Envirorisk already paid the R 15 000 to the department for the Dysselsdorp Re-Power (Pty) Ltd project company. An overview is available of the following: \r\n•	Development plan; Capital expenditure; Operational costs; Assessment of financial returns; Identification of development risks; Commercial experience; and Forward planning. We have considered potential revenue streams, operational costs, funding mixes, taxation implications and replacement requirements as a basis to inform the financial returns that could accrue to potential investors. In addition, various supplementary and complementary processes are completed (e.g. ROD is eminent and we await final decision by August 2013, Eskom Grid connection confirmed and await cost letter, plant design and pricing completed, etc) as part of the planning and statutory bidding requirements. \r\n1.	Key Assumptions: It is envisaged that all permitting and funding processes will be completed by August 2013. \r\n1.2	Project: The Dysselsdorp Solar Project entails 75MWp (DC). Eskom, the South African Power Utility confirmed that only 60MWp (AC) could be fed into the grid at Dysselsdorp. The size of the plant proposed accounts for losses with a final output of 60MWp (AC). The full capacity of the Dysselsdorp substation will be utilized as a consequence. \r\n1.3	Project location: The location for the plant is the Western Cape Province of South Africa.  The town of Oudtshoorn in the Klein Karoo is 24km for the site earmarked for the Solar Plant.  The identified land portions cover 398 ha of which 155 ha is secured through a Notarial Lease and will be used for the establishment of the Solar Plant. The existing Eskom sub-station is located adjacent to the property, which is a key consideration.\r\n1.4	Assumptions and Local content: The assessment of the project was informed by the following: a.	The Dysselsdorp community is a critical Rural Development node in the Karoo with a jobless factor of 67%. This pushed the developing team to the drawing board for solutions of how this money could be of greater benefit to the community.  Manufacturing was the only option that will benefit the community on a long term basis and will create a sustainable future for the area. We specifically designed the project and named it after the community that will benefit by it. \r\nThe Dysselsdorp Project is a 30% community project and will facilitate a array structure manufacturing facility for the Dysselsdorp community.  The business model was designed by the development team to secure job creation. The array manufacturing facility will facilitate direct jobs for 32 full time operators. It will be able to supply 48 builders and 240 laborers of material to build up their community. This exclude the jobs created for the PV development. \r\nDepartment of Rural development support the project fully and the Oudtshoorn Municipality incorporated the program into their IDP plan, as the project addresses their social and economic upliftment mandate 100%. This project will address Government strategy for this community.  \r\nb.	The project maximization in terms of scope is a requirement in order to ensure satisfactory levels of job-creation during construction and operations with a 30% community participation in the project. The latter also supports economic upliftment and job creation targets of the Oudtshoorn municipality in the Karoo.  Clinics, Housing and Schools are very urgent needs for these communities, while community upliftment is supported by involvement of the community in the project through co-ownership (Black Economic Empowerment) and sustainable funds flow for the said projects. \r\nc.	The third bidding round of the Department of Energy is earmarked as the target.\r\nSocial Recommendations. Significant job creation criteria are part of the South African Renewable Energy Program and we as a development team envisage that this will set the new benchmark for these kind of developments.\r\n\r\nIt is highly recommended that we enter into a negotiations on an ad hoc basis for this project to start in 2015.\r\n\r\nThank you for the opportunity\r\nGert Linde\r\nDirector. \r\n \r\n', 'Other', '', '', '', 'PV', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '75', '75', '60', '5.7', '1.30', 'full', '79.9', '', '', '', 'Quater3', '2015', 'we want to start construction 2 months after PPA is signed. We will take 14 moths to complete construction, where after we will start commercial operation.', '18', 'none', '12', '365', '14', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '1480', '20', '194812800', 'PWC will revert', 'PWC will revert', 'no', '40% rand based', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', 'too early to establish this detail 100%. Time may differ. we want to conclude all requirements as soon as possible to start operation at all parties involved at the earliest date possible. ', '4', '16', 'Pegasus Energy Development ( Pty ) Ltd (previously Envirorisk)', 'Pegasus Construction (Pty) Ltd', 'Pegasus Energy Development (Pty) Ltd and Community Investment Holdings', 'Pegasus Energietechnik AG ', 'Participation in the Dysselsdorp Re-Power 75MW Solar Energy project: We thank you for the invitation extended to Pegasus Construction (Pty) Ltd to participate as the EPC Contractor in the Dysselsdorp Re-Power (Pty)Ltd Solar Energy project (“the project”).                                We have accepted your offer and we have pleasure in confirming our participation in the project. Please find our work experience confirmation as follows:\r\nEPC Experience\r\nPegasus responsibilities on these 