(72, 227, 'New Power Generation ', '0768892904', 'Neville Graham', '7 Orphan ', '7', 'Orphan', 'Cape Town', 'Cape Town', '8001', 'nevillepgraham@gmail.com', 'NPG-1', 'tbc', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2013-07-03', '0000-00-00', ''),
(73, 97, 'SANJAY DYMOND', '0718904778', 'SANJAY DYMOND', 'C/O DYMONDS', '85', 'FLEET STREET', 'WESTCLIFF, CHATSWORTH', 'DURBAN', '4092', 'sanjay.dymond@gmail.com', 'PROJECT MASAI', 'Project MASAI involves the installtion of an OPEN CYCLE GAS TURBINE PLANT (OCGT). The total capacity of the plant is 150MW WITH 3 INTEGRATED MODULAR units of 50MW each. The project is currently at a PRE-BANKABKLE FEASIBILITY STAGE. The OCGT plant is a demonstration unit and has completed 6500 operating hours and is available immediatley as part of a fast track option for the IPP project using Natural Gas a fuel source. The project will be funded using a LSTK BOOM model. The project will be EXECUTED within 18 months or sooner from the date of IPP Licence and Agreement AWARD and will cost approximately USD140million.\r\n\r\nThe plant operates on NATURAL GAS with a GAS CONSUMPTION BASE LOAD of 12.910Nm3/hr per GAS TURBINE,\r\n\r\nKEY MILESTONES:\r\n1. Completion of the BANKABLE FEASIBILITY STUDY.\r\n2. IPP Licence and AGREEMENT with DOE.\r\n3. OFFTAKE AGREEMENT with ESKOM as per IPP Incentive Strategy.\r\n4. NATURAL GAS SUPPLY agreement from PETROSA or SASOL.\r\n5. EIA and Community Involvement as per the Economic Job Creation Model.\r\n6. JV Consortium agreement is applicable.\r\n7. Finalise Funding, Project Finance Strategy and Agreements.\r\n8. Government Approvals.\r\n9. Project Execution Strategy.\r\n10. Agreement to Operate - "Go Live"\r\n\r\nPrimary Equipment Supply Description\r\n3 x 50MW - GE LM 6000PC Sprint\r\n11 kV, 50 Hz, Gas Turbine Generators\r\nGas Turbine : General Electric LM6000-PC Sprint\r\nOutput : 50,000 kW\r\nSpeed : 3000 rpm, 8,495 Btu/kWh\r\nFuel : gas (675 psi +/- 20 psi)\r\nYear : 2004-2005\r\nStart : 200 hp electro-hydraulic\r\nControls : GE Mk VI + Fanuc 90/70 sequencer\r\nVibration : Bentley Nevada 3500\r\nHours : peaking duty only\r\nGenerator : Brush\r\nVoltage : 11 / 150 / 400 kV\r\nFrequency : 50 Hz\r\nPower factor : 0.9\r\nSpeed : 3000 rpm\r\n\r\nGas Turbine\r\nGeneral Electric gas turbine model LM6000 consists of a five-stage low-pressure\r\ncompressor, a fourteen-stage high pressure compressor, a two-stage high-pressure\r\nturbine, and a five-stage low pressure turbine.\r\nThe engine is equipped with a stainless steel mesh screen in the inlet air stream for\r\n"last chance" protection against foreign object damage.\r\nThe engine is shock mounted and shipped in position, with the exception of the\r\ncoupling spacer, which is removed and shipped in a separate container.\r\n\r\nAir cooled generator\r\n2 pole GE alternator rated at 71,176 KVA @ 0.90 pf, (15 C) cooling air, 11,000 volts,\r\n50 Hz, capable of handling the full continuous power of the gas turbine at any\r\nambient temperature throughout the operating range.\r\nThe generator includes a brushless excitation system with permanent magnet\r\ngenerator. Neutral and line side cubicles are included.\r\n\r\nMain Load Gearbox\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with a single-stage, vertical offset,\r\nparallel shaft speed reducer with a gear rated HP of 70,000 (52,200 kW) from a\r\ngas turbine speed of 3627 RPM to a generator speed of 3600 RPM. This unit is\r\nmanufactured and tested in accordance with API 613 3rd Edition April 1988. The\r\nactual AGMA Service Factor is 1.35. The API service factor is 1.1\r\nThe unit design includes a fabricated steel housing, clockwise rotation with pinion on\r\ntop, double helical precision carburized ground gear elements, split steel backed\r\nbabbitt lined journal bearings on all shafts and a low speed quill shaft.\r\n\r\nBaseplate\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with the support structures for the\r\ngas turbine generator set consisting of a two piece skid assembly, which is\r\nsectioned between the gas turbine and the generator. The full depth, bolted\r\nsection is designed to provide the full structural properties of the wide flange Ibeams.\r\nFull depth cross members are utilized to provide for a rigid design that\r\nis suitable for installation in earthquake areas (U.S. Seismic Zone 4) as well\r\nas providing a convenient structure for transportation. The baseplate support\r\nsystem is enhanced by the installation of a heavy-duty, welded superstructure\r\nthat utilizes structural tubing for wall columns and roof beams.\r\n\r\nAir Inlet System\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with a modular, multi-stage filtration\r\nsystem consisting of inlet screens, a pre-filter and a final barrier filter. All air for\r\nventilation systems is filtered to the same level as turbine combustion air.\r\nAn anti-ice system, evaporative cooling, combustion air heating or chilling are\r\navailable as options. Filtered air is silenced before entering the turbine plenum. This\r\ndesign results in a compact arrangement and eliminates the need for customer\r\nsupplied inlet ducting when the standard design is utilized.\r\nInternal lighting of the filter house is provided to facilitate inspection and service.\r\nPackage is also supplied with platforms and ladders to service the inlet filter. These\r\nitems are packaged separately for shipment. (Ladders, platforms and stairways to\r\nservice other portions of the gas turbine generator enclosure are not included).\r\n\r\nPiping Connections\r\nThe standard package design is supplied with the utility piping connections on the\r\nright hand side (looking from generator end) of the Unit enclosure.\r\n\r\nTurbine Exhaust\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with a circular, axial exhaust outlet with\r\nconnection flange to facilitate in-line mounting of an HRSG or simple cycle exhaust\r\nstack.\r\n\r\nFuel System\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with a natural gas fuel system using an\r\nelectronically controlled fuel metering valve. For full-load operation, the gaseous fuel\r\nmust be supplied to the baseplate at 46.5 Bar k1.4 bar. All necessary shutoff valves,\r\npiping and instruments between the baseplate connection and the engine are\r\nincluded. Gas fuel must meet General Electric specification MID-TD-0000-1.\r\n\r\nLube Oil Systems\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with two separate lube oil systems: one for\r\nthe gas turbine and one for the gear box/ generator. The oil reservoirs and piping are\r\nall stainless steel, and the lube oil system valves have stainless steel trim. Each lube\r\noil system has duplex filters, duplex shell and tube coolers, and thermostatic\r\ncontrolled electric heaters. The coolers, oil reservoir, and filters for each system are\r\nmounted on an auxiliary equipment module located next to the gas turbine\r\nbaseplate. The auxiliary equipment module provides simplified piping connections\r\nand reduces customer''s installation time and costs.\r\n\r\nElectro-Hydraulic Start System\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with an electric motor driven hydraulic\r\npump assembly, filters, cooler and controls, mounted on the auxiliary equipment\r\nmodule. A hydraulic motor is also mounted on the gas turbine accessory gearbox.\r\nHydraulic hoses are furnished to connect the auxiliary equipment module and the\r\nmain base plate.\r\n\r\nFire Protection System\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with a factory installed fire protection\r\nsystem complete with optical flame detection, hydrocarbon sensing and thermal\r\ndetectors, piping and nozzles in both generator/gearbox and engine compartments.\r\nThe fire protection system includes cylinders containing C02 mounted on a separate\r\nmodule. A 24 V DC battery and charger to power the fire protection system is also\r\nincluded. All alarms and shutdowns are annunciated at the unit control panel. An\r\nalarm sounds at the turbine if the gas detectors detect high gas levels, or if the\r\nsystem is preparing to release the C02\r\n\r\nWhen the system is activated, the package shuts down, and the primary C02\r\ncylinders are discharged into the turbine and generator/gearbox compartments via\r\nmultiple nozzles, and the ventilation dampers automatically close. After a time delay\r\nand if required, the reserve supply of C02 is discharged.\r\n\r\nGas Turbine Generator Control System\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with a free-standing control panel suitable\r\nfor mounting in an indoor, non-hazardous area. The control system features an\r\nintegrated electronic fuel management system with a PLC based programmable\r\nsequencer, vibration monitor, digital meter, digital generator protective relay module\r\nand an HMI (human machine interface) display of key discrete and analog data. The\r\noperator selects HMI displays with convenient touch screen control. Alarm and\r\nshutdown events are displayed on the HMI automatically. An Ethernet TCPIIP EGD\r\nor RS485 Modbus Port is provided to transmit unit conditions (status, pressures,\r\ntemperature, etc.) to the customer''s distributed control can be furnished to provide\r\nhard copy records. Power for the control panel is provided by a dedicated 24V DC\r\nbattery system with dual 100% capacity chargers.\r\n\r\nGenerator Protective Relays\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with a microprocessor-based generator\r\nprotective relay module, mounted in the turbine control panel. Protective relay\r\nsystem includes functions necessary for protection of the generator.\r\nComponent Testing and Package Full Load Test\r\n\r\nThe generator is tested to ANSI C50.14 or IEC 34.3 standards at its factory of\r\nmanufacture. The gas turbine is performance tested at a GE test facility.\r\nGE Aero Energy runs a "full load string test" on units with new design modifications\r\nand on selected units from each production run. All other gas turbine generator sets\r\nreceive a rigorous 400-point test including:\r\nSwitch State (NO or NC, actuation, wiring, and set point)\r\nTemperature element output, and wiring\r\nTransmitter range, output, and wiring\r\nSolenoid operation\r\nControl valve torque motor, excitation, and return signal\r\nFire system continuity, and device actuation\r\nSystem flushing verification\r\nTubing integrity\r\nDrawings, Data and Manuals\r\n\r\nThe basic equipment package is supplied with a customer drawing package that\r\nincludes general arrangement drawings, flow and instrument diagrams, electrical\r\none-line drawings and interconnection plan. Additional electrical schematic diagrams\r\nand other drawings are provided for record. Maintenance manuals are provided.', 'GasPlant', 'OCGT', 'ExistingGas', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '150', '50', '145', '75', '0.85', 'CPI', '50%', '', '', '', 'Quater3', '2015', 'TO BE ADVISED', '18', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '1400000000', '30', '8.50', '', 'CPI', 'yes', '', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', '', '6', '18', 'BIOSIGMA CONSORTIUM', 'GENERAL ELECTRIC', 'DISCUSSIONS ARE IN PROGRESS WITH SUITABLE CONSORTIUM PARTNERS', 'TO BE ADVISED (PROJECT FUNDER IS BASED IN HONG KONG AND WILL TAKE PARTIAL EQUITY IN THE PROJECT)', 'TO BE ADVISED', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 100, 'TO BE ADVISED', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '6', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '6', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '6', '', 'draft', 'yes', 'NOT APPLICABLE, NATURAL GAS WILL BE SUPPLIED BY AN EXISTING LNG SUPPLIER IN SOUTH AFRICA', 'PORT ELIZABETH', 'E25', '41', '19.32', 'S33', '48', '11.16', 'no', '', 'no', 'no', '', 'yes', '28/02/2014', '30/06/2014', 'no', '', '', 'COMPETITION COMMISSION, EIA, ESKOM, CDC, DOE, NERSA, ', '1', 'E25', '41', '19.32', 'S33', '48', '11.16', 'COEGA DEDISA SUBSTATION, DME OCGT Integration at Dedisa 400kV ', 'no', '', '', '', 'TO BE ADVISED, DISCUSSIONS ARE PROGRESSING VIA THE CDC WITH ESKOM', 'TO BE ADVISED, MINOR UPGRADE WILL BE REQUIRED.', 'TO BE ADVISED, ESKOM CONNECTION.', '18', 'NOT APPLICABLE', '75-85', '700000000', '50.00', 'TO BE ADVISED, DISCUSSIONS IN PROGRESS', '500', 'TO BE ADVISED, DISCUSSIONS IN PROGRESS', '2013-07-03', '2013-07-12', 'true'),
(74, 115, 'Exxaro Reductants (Pty) Ltd', '0123074243', 'Jan Oberholzer', 'Exxaro Corporate Centre', '1', 'Roger Dyason Road', 'Pretoria West', 'Pretoria', '0183', 'Jan.Oberholzer@Exxaro.com', 'Lephalale Non-Recovery Coke Oven Cogeneration Plant', 'Waste-heat will be recovered from a non-recovery coke making plant from a supply of Semi Soft Coking coal (SSCC) at Grootegeluk Coal Mine near Lephalale. This plant will convert the waste heat from the flue gases produced by the coke plant into steam feeding a cogeneration plant adjacent to it for the purposes of electricity generation.\r\n\r\nThe fundamental cost drivers for this project are when the non-recovery coke plant will be built, the capital cost of equipment to be purchased for the construction of the plant, the cost of construction and operation of the necessary facility for the treatment of flue gas, ie. desulphurisation, as well as the maintenance and operational costs of the plant inclusive of the personnel requirements, spares and consumables and water treatment capability \r\n\r\nDecision points\r\nIn lieu of the progress of the project the decision steps remaining are primarily Exxaro board approval for the capital and business requirements for the implementation of the project. This is dependent and motivated on the content of the bankable feasibility study, which is complete and currently under internal review. The Pre-Feasibility Studies (PFS) and Environmental Authorisation for the plants have already been obtained.\r\n ', 'Cogeneration', 'Integrated', 'other32', '', '', '', 'Waste heat boilers convert the flue gas heat for steam production with turbine alternator sets converting steam to electricity ', '', '', '', '', '', '120', '30', '100', '85', '0.82', 'NERSA MYPD', '', '35', '', '', 'Quater4', '2017', 'Linked to commercial approval of Non-Recovery Coke Project at Grootgeluk Mine.', '36', 'baseload', '12', '312', '24', 'yes', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '1750', '30', '820', 'To be determined (Carbon-Tax, etc..)', 'NERSA MYPD', 'yes', '', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', '', '6', '36', 'Exxaro Reductants (Pty) Ltd', 'To be determined', 'Exxaro Reductants (Pty) Ltd', 'None', 'Exxaro Reductants has completed construction of cogeneration plant at the Namakwa Sands Plant. This is the first co-generation plant constructed by the company and it shall be operated by Exxaro . The construction has been completed successfully and the commissioning of the plant is in progress. Exxaro Resources is the second largest coal producer in South Africa and largest supplier to ESKOM. Eight fully managed coal mines and one 50:50 joint venture operation produce about 50 million tons per annum of power station, steam and coking coal. All of the power station coal is supplied to the national power utility, Eskom, and municipal power stations. Exxaro Resources has also completed and commissioned 13.6MW Co-gen project at Exxaro’s Namakwa Sands operations in the Northern Cape which Co-gen facility is currently under construction and scheduled to produce 100GWh by 2014. Exxaro Resources is also a 50/50 shareholder in Cennergi (together with Tata Power) which was successful in achieving Financial Close in two wind projects totalling 239-MW under the DOE''s rolling renewable energy independent power producer procurement programme (REIPPPP).', '17040000000', '20961000000', '16121000000', 'yes', '', '', '', '', 51, 'The main shareholders in Exxaro are Exxaro’s empowerment partners (54.1%) through a black economic empowerment holding company, the broad based employee share option plan, Anglo American and a minority shareholder free float of on the JSE.\r\n\r\nThe empowerment partners consisting of Eyesizwe shareholders, members of the empowerment consortia (Tiso, Eyabantu and Basadi ba Kopane) and the IDC became shareholders in the holding company of Exxaro (BEE Holdco) – making Exxaro one of the largest black-owned, controlled and managed companies in South Africa. \r\nJURIE CAN WE PROVIDE MORE INFO ON WATERBERG SOCIAL & LABOUR PLAN', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'no', 'no', 'no', '6', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', '01/10/2017', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', '', 'no', 'Non-Recovery Coke plant from which waste-heat to be sourced has yet to be constructed. Environmental Authorisation as attached (ANNEXURE-D)', 'Q4 2017', 'ANNEXURE-A', 'ANNEXURE-A', '6', 'corporate', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '6', 'yes', 'draft', 'no', 'All Pre-Feasibility Studies (PFS) have been completed. The Bankable Feasibility Study (BFS) is in process. No additional studies are required due to own funding mechanism employed for this project, with coal-supply to the Non-Rceovery Coke facility having at least a 40-year life-expectancy.', 'Lephalale, Waterberg District Municipality, Limpopo Province', '27', '34', '10', '23', '39', '19', 'yes', 'This plant will be built in the Grootgeluk Mine Area. This plant shall be constructed on the property of Grootegeluk coal mine which is property owned by Exxaro Resources, as per attached Location Plan (ANNEXURE-C).', 'yes', 'yes', '', 'no', '', '11/07/2014', 'no', '', '', 'Air Emissions License (Q4 2013), NERSA License (Q4 2014), Grootgeluk Mine Water-Use License amendment and EMP amendment (Q4 2014)', '3', '27', '34', '10', '23', '39', '19', 'Grootgeluk Main Substation (P.C.C.)', 'no', '', '', '', 'Only preliminary discussions have been held, and upgrades are envisaged along with two-way metering facilities.', 'No major upgrade to transmission lines or connections forseen.', 'Eskom', '24', 'None', '65-75', '634', '25.01', 'Preference to be given to local Lephalale suppliers, then Limpopo based suppliers, then national suppliers and thereafter after other suppliers. To the extent possible a target of 50% local SA content will be pursued, particularly with regard to labour, civils, piping and structural trades.', '320', 'This may be difficult for such a small projects to achieve due to the lack of economies of scale, as most of the high-technology equipment will be imported.Will utilise existing Exxaro training facilities in Lephalale.', '2013-07-03', '2013-07-12', 'true'),
(75, 71, 'XEnOPTA Holdings (Pty) Ltd. trading as EnOPTA', '+27 11 678 7188', 'Seth Olivier', 'Building 1', '21 ', 'Ethel Ave.', 'Northcliff', 'Johannesburg', '2195', 'setho@enopta.net', 'Salnova power station', 'EnOPTA has developed an IPP (Independent Power Producer) solution that consists of an 800 MW, Open cycle base load, Natural Gas fired power plant. The plan is to erect the plant on the ArcelorMittal Saldanha Steel site, giving access to existing grid networks and will alleviate supply pressures in the Western Cape.\r\n\r\nEver rising cost of Electricity and Carbon materials are driving Industry beyond their economical tipping point.  The prime objective of this project is to ensure security of supply to current intensive electricity users in the Saldanha area e.g. ArcelorMittal at a highly competitive predictable price regime. \r\n\r\nThe Power plant will go a long way to stabilize the Western Cape Grid and afford ESKOM the window to address the current supply shortage. The location of the IPP will reduce electricity supply losses due to long inland transmission lines. Additional base load will enable connection of new Industries in the planned IDZ ( Industrial Development Zone). New load connections are currently unavailable, holding up direct investment opportunities into the IDZ. \r\n\r\n. \r\nPROJECT DESCRIPTION \r\n\r\nThe project will supply the needs of ArcelorMittal Saldanha Steel and the excess electricity (+/-640MW) will be made available to industries within the IDZ or sold to Eskom, and/or Municipalities within the Western Cape Province, at competitive rates. An MOU has been signed with ArcelorMittal.\r\n\r\n \r\nFUEL SUPPLY \r\n\r\nNatural gas in the form of Compressed Natural Gas (CNG) will be supplied by ship to the port of Saldanha, where it will be offloaded via a submersible pipeline either from a mooring area located off shore or a birthing location in the harbor in Saldanha. The Natural Gas is compressed on site at the well head, from African supply countries (Angola, Tanzania and Nigeria), and stored in specially designed containers on dedicated ships. The CNG ship will act as the storage facility in port. All technology has successfully undergone full due-diligence by independent third party specialists and demonstrated in practice.\r\n \r\n\r\nPOWER PLANT EQUIPMENT /OPERATIONS / MAINTENANCE\r\n\r\nThe plant will consist of 950MW installed capacity, with 800MW available on a 24 hour basis. \r\n\r\nThe equipment chosen for the project consists of the following: \r\n\r\n	7 X 115MW brand new GE FRAME 9 PG171-E’s (AT PORT READY FOR SHIPMENT)\r\n	The FRAME 9’s will be used for base load power\r\n	3 X 43MW completely refurbished with GE Guarantees GE LM6000’s\r\n	The LM6000’s will be used during peaking periods\r\n\r\nEnOPTA, through its International partnerships brings the expertise to deliver, install, operate and maintain the power plant for the life of the power plant.  The power plant will be fully installed within 12 to 18 months from completion  of the EIA’s and financial closing. (Approximately 36 months from start)\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'GasPlant', 'CCGT', 'other31', '', '', '', '', 'Tri-fuel: LNG, CNG, Fuel oil/diesel ', '', '', '', '', '934', '115', '794', '85', '0.69', 'Linked to NERSA approved tariff increases to Eskom and a component linked to international gas price (negotiable)', 'The thermal electrical-efficiency of the plant in simple cycle is 37.1% and in combined cycle is 52.7%', '', '', '', 'Quater3', '2015', 'Assuming 6 month EIA', '18', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '7120 ', '20', '73', 'Our price is a flat rate per MWh and does not include any wheeling costs. The price per MW is based off of the full-off take of the plant.', 'Linked to NERSA approved tariff increases to Eskom and a component linked to international gas price (negotiable)', 'no', '60% linked to USA dollar price of Natural Gas', 'fastQ2-2013-24Month', '', '3', '18', 'International Power Consortium South Africa (IPCSA)', 'General Electric through Power & Combustion Services Africa Inc.', 'XEnOPTA holdings (Pty) Ltd. Trading as EnOPTA', 'Power & Combustion Services Africa Inc.', 'The International Power Consortium South Africa team involved in completing this project have been involved in power plant construction and operations and maintenance for over 60 years. Power & Combustion Services USA division comprises of several international contractors and subcontractors that have design engineered and installed power plants of this size and capacity world wide:(for example):\r\n     •	Millmeran Power project 800MW (Brisbane, Australia)\r\n     •	Redhills Power Generation Facility 440MW (Mississippi, USA)\r\n     •	Baijo Power Project 1 950MW Combined cycle (Mexico)\r\nIncluded in the overall services that Power & Combustion Services provide, comes over 60 years of Operations and Maintenance (O&M) experience where PCS USA division performs O&M for over 60 IPP''s world wide including India, Trinidad, Tobago and the USA:\r\n     •	PEPCO Energy Services 275MW simple cycle HFO (Arlington, Virginia USA)\r\n     •	North American Energy Service 550MW (Washington, DC USA)\r\n     •	National Institute of Health 23MW Cogeneration Facility (Bethesda, MD USA)\r\n     •	GE energy Birchwood power facility 250MW coal (King George, VA USA\r\n     •	International experience includes O&M contracts in Chile, Trinidad, Tobago with facilitating training facilities for O&M contractors in the Philippines. \r\n     •	Experience also includes boiler making for ArcelorMittal USA, Baltimore USA\r\n\r\nThe members of EnOPTA have been involved in large scale energy, IT and maintenance projects in Africa for over 30 years, with combined experience in the following:\r\n     •	Electrical transmission and distribution – AC and DC generation inter-connectors for:\r\n            o	Eskom\r\n            o	Mozambique\r\n            o	Zimbabwe\r\n            o	Zambia\r\n            o	Namibia\r\n            o	Botswana\r\n     •	Electrical generation power systems protection control automation with turn-key design engineering for balance of plant with Siemans:\r\n            o	Majuba\r\n            o	Kendall\r\n            o	Matla\r\n            o	Kariba\r\n            o	Ketse dam distribution substation\r\n     •	Operational management experience in large scale maintenance scheduling and facilities for Pratt & Whitney and Garret turbines.\r\n     •	Management of large IT and on-line banking system implementation projects: e.g.\r\n            o	Natal Building Society – 1974 - 1977\r\n            o	Anglo American Technical Services – 1985 - 1987\r\n     •	Management of large consulting and organisational change projects: e.g.\r\n            o	ISCOR – 1996 - 1998\r\n            o	Transnet – 2006 - 2008\r\n            o	Rand Refinery – 2008 - 2009\r\n     •	Director of Companies\r\n     •	MSc. MBA \r\n     •	Environmental protection services with Government agencies', '1500000000', '1800000000', '1900000000', 'yes', '', '', '', '', 26, 'A fundamental aspect of the project, and part of the agreement with the primary electricity off-taker, is that the project directly provides benefits to the local community of Saldanha Bay.  This will manifest in the following way:\r\n1.	The primary off-taker for the electricity will be the ArcelorMittal Saldanha Steel plant (160MW base load, up to 230MW peaking load).   This will immediately reduce the load on ESKOM.\r\n2.	The excess electricity will be available to support economic development of the Saldanha IDZ, which is currently turning prospective investors away (e.g. smelters, mineral processing plants) because ESKOM cannot supply the electricity needed.  The 800MW plant will have between 570MW and 640MW of power available to off-takers in the IDZ at prices equal to or less than Megaflex..\r\n3.	The plant can provide the 40MW that the local municipality needs, also at economic rates.\r\n4.	Local direct job creation during construction, for on-going operation and maintenance, local training.\r\n5.	The SPV that will be established will create an employee share trust through which local employees of the plant and their dependents will benefit directly from the plant profits. This share trust will hold a material share in the SPV.\r\n6.	The investors will be developing a service center that will also provide jobs, training and provide service support on turbines and engines to local industry.\r\n7.     A Community Trust will be formed that will create a local training bursary fund for technical education and will provide channels to support local community development initiatives. \r\n', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', '3', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '01/01/2015', 'no', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2', 'project', '', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '3', '', 'draft', 'yes', 'Preliminary feasibility studies have been completed, but the following detailed work is outstanding:\r\n1.	Environmental impact assessment \r\n2.	Some geological testing of the site\r\n3.	Confirmation of utilities at site.\r\n4.	Co-operative study with ESKOM of the grid interface and network stabilisation requirements\r\n5.	Studies with the Saldanha Port Authority regarding gas off-loading both off-shore and at quay.  Location of undersea pipeline from off-shore storage to on-shore storage.\r\n6.	Confirmation of land zoning.\r\n7.	Confirmation of usage of the existing ArcelorMittal servitude from the plant to the harbour.\r\n8.	Port arrangements for the delivery and off-loading of turbines and heavy equipment\r\n9.	Finalisation of roadway  load capabilities\r\n10.	Gas supply source: finalisation of off-take agreement based on final demand requirements at Saldanha.\r\n11.	Gas shipping: finalisation of shipping contract based on PPA \r\n12.	Gas storage: finalisation of site requirements, regulatory approval.\r\n', 'Arcelor Mittal, Saldanha, Western Cape, South Africa', '18', '02', '04', '32', '59', '10', 'yes', 'Land has been secured through a MOU with ArcelorMittal and we are currently in negotiations on a Long-term Lease from ArcelorMittal who are the property owners and primary off-taker for the power.\r\n \r\n', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', '1.	IPP licence (NERSA) - 3 months\r\n2.	Gas import licence - 3 months\r\n3.	Gas storage approval - 3 months\r\n4.	IDZ registration (investment etc) - 1 month\r\n5.	Agreements with Port Authority - 1 - 3 month\r\n6.	Local business trading licences - 1 month                                                                                                                                                                       \r\n7.     Confirm land zoning conditions - 1 month', '2', '18', '02', '53', '32', '58', '55', 'Blouwater substation ', 'no', '', '', '', 'In January 2013 we met with Divisional Executive (Office of the Chief Executive) Kannan Lakmeeharan and presented the opportunity of providing the country with 2 GW base load power generated from Natural Gas. We were then asked to submit a proposal, which was submitted in February 2013. From there we met again with the Divisional Executives office and were requested to present to Senior Executives on the 8th of April 2013. On the 8th of April 2013 we presented to Senior Executives including Dan Marokane (Group Executive Technology & Commercial). Since then we have had meetings with the Senior Manager Project Development Department in regards to the project development.', 'Not required', 'Eskom', '12', 'N/A', '65-75', '2095', '29.93', 'A full service center, consequential industrialization of the Saldanha IDZ. Example: Manganese smelter can be built, Rare earth refinement can be fully supported.', '2000', 'Opportunities fall into two categories:\r\n1.	Directly associated with the power plant.\r\na.	Local content will be: \r\ni.	civil engineering and construction of site, buildings, roads, utilities\r\nii.	plant infrastructure including piping, wiring, switchgear, transformer rewiring\r\niii.	training centre\r\niv.	increased use of the Port at Saldanha\r\n2.	Indirect benefits and job creation:\r\na.	Supply of power to IDZ that is not currently available will stimulate local economy and attract local manufacture and beneficiation \r\nb.	Increase use of Port\r\nc.	Broader economic stimulus for the Western Cape Economic Development initiative.\r\nd.      Community Trust to be established to support local training (technical) through bursaries and additional support of community development initiatives', '2013-07-03', '2013-07-11', 'true');
