(83, 208, 'Mega Africa Holdings (Pty) Ltd', '082 805 3045', 'Malose Ledwaba', 'Unit 102, Kingston House, Hampton Office Park', '20', 'Georgian Crescent East', 'Bryanston', 'Johannesburg', '2050', 'business@mega-africa.co.za', 'Lengau Power Project', 'The Lengau Power IPP is a 300MW CFBC air cooled power plant comprising 2 x 150MW unit sizes.  It is situated in the Free State Province near a town of Vierfontein.  The uniqueness of the project promises to be the best proposal of all available potential coal-fired projects in the country.  The project combines good aspects of location, environmental loading, availability of water and proven fuel source, proximity to major Eskom transmission infrastructure, and socio economic upliftment in an economically marginalised region.  \r\nThese aspects of the project, together with unique and innovative funding results in a highly competitive tariff, a needed strengthening of the transmission network in the region, job creation and sustainable economic upliftment in the area.  \r\nThe project is a mine-mouth power station, based on coal deposits with proven thermal properties; the same deposits previously operated Eskom''s Vierfontein Power Station for thirty seven and half years.  \r\nThe Project Sponsors, Mega Africa Holdings are a substantial equity owner in the coal company and have secured supply of the coal to the power plant.  It is estimated that there is sufficient coal to operate at least a 600MW.  \r\nProject partners including: 1. International Developer(s), 2. EPC, O&M, and an Investor have committed to the project, and all these partners will play a role in fast tracking the development of the project up to financial close. \r\nIt is estimated that the project will meet a Commercial Operation Date of mid-year 2017 for both units.  \r\nThe project offers significant control to local partners in both ownership and management, and maximises the meaningful participation of broad-based economically empowered partners, 