(84, 226, 'Aldwych International Ltd', '+442077761900', 'Helen Tarnoy', '4 Longridge', '153', 'Peter Mokaba Rd', 'Morningside', 'Durban', '4001', 'jade@aldwych-international.com', 'Umbani', 'Umbani Power Company (Umbani) is proposing to develop a 540MW Fluidised Bed Boiler Power Plant in the KwaMbonambi area of KwaZulu-Natal.  The plant will use discard coal from existing and decommissioned mines in KwaZulu-Natal and Mpumalnga Provinces.  The electricity produced will be fed into Eskom''s transmission network and should result in the significant stabilisation of electricity supply in the greater City of uMhlathuze area.\r\n\r\nThe plant will comprise 4 x 135MW units which will be constructed as one phase with the units being commissioned at 3-monthly intervals.  The plant is expected to operate at baseload, with approximately 90% availability.  Total annual generated energy should be approximately 4,250 GWh.\r\n\r\nThe expected project cost is around ZAR 11 billion (2008 data). PLEASE NOTE that this project was originall prepared for the Pilot National Co-generation tender in 2008 and all data will need to be refreshed.  Some prices have eased since then.\r\n\r\nThe feasibility study has been finalised, the EIA ROD has been received from DEA, the site has been secured, equity partners are identified and Eskom has quoted for connection into a new bay at Invubu sub-station, 10 km from the site.\r\n\r\nThe time to COD is 48 months from PPA effectiveness for units 1 and 2 and 54 months for units 3 and 4.', 'Thermal', 'Coal', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '540', '135', '486', '85', '.85', 'PPI', '38-40%', '', '', '', 'Quater3', '2018', 'First 2 units 48 months, second 2 units 54 months', '48', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '11000', '25', '850', 'NB: All numbers are in 2008 Rand and will need to be refreshed.', 'SA PPI', 'yes', '', 'commitQ2-2014-Phased', '', '6', '48', 'Umbani Power Company', 'Will be tendered; 2008 bid was based on BHEL equipment', 'Rainbow Millennium Power Company (Pty) Ltd', 'Aldwych International Ltd', 'Umbani is an SPV formed for the development of the project.  Aldwych International management has experience of development, construction, financing or acquisition and operation of nearly 30 coal-fired power plants worldwide since 1985.  Aldwych is also the operator of the Kelvin power plant in Johannesburg, to our knowledge the only coal-fired IPP in South Africa.  An experience list and company profile will be attached to the hard copy of the submission.  Since Umbani is an SPV it has no turnover in the last three years (see below).', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 25, 'The proposal is to appoint the EIA Consultant to conduct a sustainable development\r\ninitiative to ensure that the Corporate Social Investment initiatives by Umbani\r\nPower are consistent with the needs of the community.', 'yes', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '6', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '6', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '6', '', 'finalised', 'yes', 'Completed. Please note, however, that all data will need to be refreshed after five years'' delay. The quoted 6 months to financial close from neing presented with a bankable PPA assumes no significant reworking of studies.', 'Mabuyeni, 5km north west of Nseleni town, near Richards Bay', '31', '58', '00', '28', '37', '00', 'yes', 'Lease agreement in place in 2008, to be refreshed.  Ngonyama Trust agreement to be reconfirmed.  Site plan attached to hard copy.', 'yes', 'yes', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'Zoning and Civil Aviation Authority approval received in 1998.', '10', '00', '00', '00', '00', '00', '00', 'Invubu 400kV', 'yes', '', 'yes', 'Attached to hard copy.  Will need to be reconfirmed.', 'Eskom (Grid Planning) quoted 23 May 2008.', 'Line will be connected into new 275kV bay at Invubu substation.', 'Eskom.', '24', 'Not applicable', '75-85', '2750', '25.00', 'Local engineering and production of all facilities within the BOP scope is planned, including demineralization and water treatment plant, auxiliary boilers and the like ', '250', 'Umbani has entered negotiations with an SA contractor, for the EPC of the power plant. The contractor has an excellent understanding of local manufacturing and delivery supply chain capabilities, in particular the ability to source services, equipment and materials with due regard to BBBEE code requirements.  This ability is proven in the numerous infrastructure and process plants executed by the contractor group.\r\nThe contractor has a well established skills development programme that includes:\r\n•	Artisan development programme – focus on the training of skilled artisans\r\n•	Supervisory development programme – focus on the development of mentor training skills to ensure an ongoing internal transfer of skills\r\n•	Trainer development programme – focus on training Supervisors and Foremen\r\n•	Graduate Development Programme – focus on transferring of skills to graduates\r\n\r\nThe balance of plant scope encompasses some significant process and plant package work including auxiliary and ancillary systems that lend themselves to localisation.  Already systems and plant such as demineralization, water treatment, auxiliary boilers and the like will be engineered in South Africa for the Umbani project and are able to be manufactured in South Africa. ', '2013-07-04', '2013-07-10', 'true'),
(85, 59, 'Tongaat Hulett Limited', '083 265 6628', 'Wolfgang Fechter', 'Tongaat Hulett Head Office', '1', 'Amanzimnyama Hill Road', 'Tongaat', 'Tongaat', '4400', 'wolfgang.fechter@tongaat.com', 'Darnall Biomass Fired Power Station', 'Historically sugar mills were designed and are currently operated on the basis that the fuel supply (sugarcane fibre) is matched with the demand for steam and electricity.  The sugar mill has its own power plant (boilers and turbo-alternators), which uses all of the bagasse fuel (sugarcane fibre) to generate steam.  This steam is used to generate electricity for use by the mill, and exhaust steam from this process is used to provide heat for the sugar manufacturing process.  Combined Heat and Power (CHP), or Cogeneration, and has been the standard for sugar mills for decades.  \r\n\r\nIn order to take advantage of the opportunities presented by electricity generation from sugarcane fibre, a project is proposed to establish a new power station, with the objective to export the maximum amount of electricity, is planned for the Darnall sugar mill owned by Tongaat Hulett Limited.  The project includes the improvement of the energy efficiency of the sugar mill in order to make more fuel available for electricity export.  Additional biomass fuels in the form of sugarcane leaves and other woody biomass will be included to extend the utilization of the power station.\r\n\r\nRefer to the attached supporting documents for a more detailed description of the project and the project development pipeline from Tongaat Hulett Limited.\r\n', 'Cogeneration', 'Integrated', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '68', '35', '62', '54.7', '0.92', 'Refer Tongaat Hulett - Amatikulu Biomass Fired Power Station', '', '22.31%', '', '', 'Quater2', '2020', 'COD will be aligned with the start of the sugar crushing season which is typically in the beginning of April every year.', '36', 'none', '8.3', '252', '24', 'no', '', 'yes', 'The existing PPA with Eskom is based on the premise that only the marginal cost of generation is rewarded and is applied to marginal spare capacity from the sugar mill available for limited operating periods.', 'yes', 'The project constitutes an improvement of the energy efficiency within the boundaries of the sugar mill, hence generating more fuel for electricity generation. The existing power station will be replaced with the latest technology option to take advantage of all the biomass fuel available and converting it as efficiently as possible to steam and electricity.', '3756', '20', '2160', 'Not Applicable', 'Refer Tongaat Hulett - Amatikulu Biomass Fired Power Station', 'yes', '', 'commitQ2-2016-Phased', 'Q3/4 2017', '54', '36', 'Tongaat Hulett Limited', 'To Be Confirmed', 'Not Applicable', 'Not Applicable', 'Project Developer (Tongaat Hulett Limited)\r\nFor a complete company profile visit www.tongaat.com. \r\nCogeneration is standard operation at sugar mills. Tongaat Hulett has the experience through many years of operating and maintaining biomass power stations at their 4 South African sugar mills and their sugar mills in Mozambique and Zimbabwe. Tongaat Hulett Limited also has been designing sugar mill processes and equipment for almost 3 decades and markets their technology internationally.\r\n', '14373000000', '12081000000', '9681000000', 'yes', '', '', '', '', 18, 'Socio-Economic Development within the context of Tongaat Hulett operations forms an integral part of the businesses activities, and is closely linked to the company’s overall objective of contributing to the creation of successful rural communities. The business has traditionally focused its SED spend on improving the quality of life of communities that surround company operations and its employees. Tongaat Hulett is now in the process of shifting this focus, to its private farmers. This shift, which is ongoing, will ensure that private farmers receive the support required for them to be sustainable into the future, and includes actions related to unlocking land for sugarcane development and grant funding from Government. A number of small scale growers derive their livelihood from delivering sugarcane to the sugar mill operating close to their agricultural operations. Tongaat Hulett has many years of experience in developing successful indigenous private farmers. Refer to the supporting document (section 6, section 8 and Appendix II) for more detail on community involvement in the ownership structure as well as enterprise development and socio-economic aspects.', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', 'yes', 'no', 'no', 'no', '54', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', '', 'no', 'Refer to Amatikulu Biomass Fired Power Station and supporting documentation (Section 5 and App V has detail on biomass supply).', 'Refer to Amatikulu Biomass Fired Power Station and supporting documentation (Section 5 and App V has detail on biomass supply).', 'Refer to Amatikulu Biomass Fired Power Station and supporting documentation (Section 5 and App V has detail on biomass supply).', 'Refer to Amatikulu Biomass Fired Power Station and supporting documentation (Section 5 and App V has detail on biomass supply).', '54', 'project', '', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '54', 'yes', 'draft', 'no', 'This will be the third project in a series of planned projects at the 4 sugar mills of the Developer (Tongaat Hulett Limited).  The lessons learned from the preceding projects, will ensure that all relevant studies are completed in time.', 'Darnall, KZN', '31', '21', '38.39', '29', '16', '15.27', 'yes', 'The site is owned by Tongaat Hulett Limited (Developer).  A Rental and Services agreement will be utilized to arrange for the use of the site by the (to be formed) SPV company wholly-owned by Tongaat Hulett.', 'no', 'yes', '24/08/2011', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'This will be the third project in a series of planned projects at the 4 sugar mills of the Developer (Tongaat Hulett Limited).  The lessons learned from the preceding projects, will ensure that all relevant authorization are obtained in time.', '1.7', '31', '22', '32.71', '29', '15', '46.49', 'Zinkwazi', 'no', '', '', '', 'Not Applicable', 'No.', 'Eskom', '30', 'Not Applicable', '75-85', '2310', '61.50', 'Refer to Tongaat Hulett - Amatikulu Biomass Fired Power Station project as well as supporting document (Section 6 & Appendix II).', '3922', 'Refer to Tongaat Hulett - Amatikulu Biomass Fired Power Station project as well as supporting document (Section 6 & Appendix II).', '2013-07-05', '2013-07-11', 'true');
