(88, 83, 'First Tech', '0826965282', 'Gina Schroeder', '11 Meadow Manor', '36', 'Meadow Lane', 'Kloof', 'Durban', '3610', 'gina@enercheck.co.za', 'Adcock Ingram Cogeneration', 'The Adcock Ingram Cogeneration Project, a project which has been in development since 2009, is one of a few select gas based generation projects still viable for completion by 2016. The projects primary drivers of clean energy production; power supply security; high efficiency technology implementation and jobs/skills creation all mutually aligned with the government objectives as stated in the IRP2010.  Using Natural Gas sourced from Egoli Gas (Sasol), the project uses high efficiency gas combustion engines, sourced from the worlds leading supplier in this technology  - Wartsila, to generate 9MW of clean electrical energy onto the grid and produces steam for use in the Adcock Ingram production facility thus off-setting their current coal burning facilities and drastically reducing the amount of emissions generated.\r\n \r\nA brief overview of each of the key project elements is provided below:\r\n1. Fuel Supply: The project is located directly on the Egoli Gas pipeline network in Aeroton, Johannesburg. Egoli have confirmed that sufficient gas is available in the network to supply this project without any upgrades or modifications to the network. The prices of the fuel will be as per the recently approved gas prices from NERSA.\r\n\r\n2. Land Ownership: The plant will be located on Adcock Ingrams factory premises in Aeroton, Johannesburg, South Africa. An undeveloped piece of land adjacent to their factory operations and the existing gas pipeline is sufficiently large enough to accomodate the full cogeneration facility. No leasing charges will be applicable as Adcock Ingram are the steam off-takers for the project.\r\n\r\n3. Grid Connection: The power will be evacuated through the existing Adcock Ingram grid onto City Powers grid system. Through discussions held with City Power, there is sufficient capacity in the Aeroton grid to sustain the generation of 9MW in this area. The nearest substation for connection is located less than 1km away from the facility. \r\n\r\n4. EPC: Wartsila has shown in interest in acting as the primary equipment supplier and potentially also the EPC contractor for this project. In the event where Wartsila wont be the EPC contractor; alternative local contractors have been identified that will assume the EPC responsibility. (Refer to attachments of Wartsila experience and capabilities) \r\n\r\n5. Steam Offtaker: Adcock Ingram will act as the primary steam off-taker for the project which will allow them to reduce their reliance on coal fired boilers to generate their steam. \r\n\r\n6. Lenders/Equity: No lenders have yet been approached for this project. First Tech may consider taking an equity stake however, finalization of both lenders and equity partners can only be considered upon confirming the off-taker for the power.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe main cost drivers for this project resides in the gas price. The gas industry has recently undergone significant changes transitioning from the ''Market Value Pricing'' structure to a non-discriminatory ''Maximum Price'' model as approved by NERSA. Through these new gas pricing regulations, the gas price and escalation mechanisms are clearly defined for this project. \r\n\r\nThe primary trigger required to initiate further development and to reach Financial Close for the project is the presentation of a bankable PPA. Upon receiving a bankable PPA, additional funds and resources will be allocated to ensure a timeous completion of the project.\r\n', 'Cogeneration', 'CogenerationReciprocating', 'other32', 'Gas', '', '', 'Natural Gas sourced from Egoli (which is sourced from Sasol''s Natural Gas network)', '', '', '', '', '', '9.7', '9.7', '8', '85', '1.4', '6', '', '70', '', '', 'Quater1', '2016', '', '22', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '155', '20', '140', '', '6', 'yes', '', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', '', '4', '22', 'First Tech', 'Wartsila', '(First Tech is a South African Entity)', 'Not Applicable', 'The reader is directed below and to the attachment in the RFRI submission for comprehensive details on the experience of the developers, First Tech, and the equipment suppliers, Wartsila.                                                                                                        First Tech Experience                                                                                                    - Belle Vue Mapou Mauritius 72 MW, role-co-developer and EPC Contractor (for Duke Engineering)\r\n- Bell Bay Repowering for Duke Energy in Tasmania\r\n- Synchronous Condenser Richards Bay Minerals as part of a 160MW power plant\r\n- Newcastle Cogeneration project 15 MW 100 tph steam for IPSA\r\n- 600 MW Coal Fired Power Station in Mozambique (under development)\r\n- 600 MW Temane combined cycle project Mozambique (GDF Suez)\r\n- DoE , 1,000 MW Open Cycle Gas Turbine Project (GDF Suez)\r\n- Elgas Acquisition and expansion to 2.4 MW (2010/2011) – Expanding to 15 MW (own, operate and maintain)\r\n- Development of BioTherm Energy Renewable Energy Projects under REFIT                          Wartsila Experience                                                                                                         - Over 4500MW installed in 350 power stations for CHP on gas in 38 countries                                                                            ', '45000000', '50000000', '70000000', 'no', '', '', '', '', 30, 'We have developed an emporment strategy which can be referred to in the attachments. Our main objectives are:                                                                                                         1)	To have greater broad-based involvement\r\n2)	To have our empowerment partners co-invest alongside the developers\r\n3)	To have our  empowerment partners actively engaged at SPV Level\r\n', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '', 'no', '6', 'yes', 'no', 'yes', '02/02/2015', 'no', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '6', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '8', '', 'draft', 'no', 'No additional fuel source studies that may be required by the lenders are envisaged at this stage. As the fuel (Natural Gas) is sourced from Egoli, who acts as a distributor for Sasol Natural Gas in Johannesburg, the reliability and availability of supply is dependent on Sasol''s upstream operations and their respective access to gas either from Mozambique or elsewhere. This particular supply of fuel has been in existence for many years and is known to be a secure source of energy and is intended to be as such for at least the lifetime of the plant. If any studies were to be conducted, they may revolve around the reliability of supply on the Aeroton piped network and also the long term pricing indices related to the gas (as defined by NERSA).', 'Aeroton, Johannesburg, Gauteng, South Africa', '27', '58', '38', '26', '15', '20', 'yes', 'The project site resides within the boundaries of the Adcock Ingram Aeroton Facility. Adcock Ingram are in agreement with the developers that the project will be located on their site. As Adcock are the primary steam off-takers, there will be no leasing costs applicable (any leasing costs would be transferred into the steam tariff hence there is no need to include a seperate leasing cost for this project). The reader is referred to the attachments on the hardcopy submission which indicates the project location and plant layout. ', 'yes', 'yes', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'NERSA Generation Licence - 6 months;                                                                              Name change on Environmental Authorisation - 3 months (As the project falls below the 10tph fuel consumption and the 10MW generator thresholds stated in the Environmental Legislation, the project only needs to be registered with the local municipality; i.e. City of Joburg, for authorisation. To date, the project is registered but in a different name to what the name of the SPV will be.', '0.6', '27', '58', '44', '26', '15', '33', 'Langa 11kV Substation', 'yes', '03/07/2013', 'no', '', 'A number of preliminary technical meetings have been held with City Power regarding the connection requirements for this project. ', 'The reader is referred to the City Power Single Line Diagram attached to the hard copy submission for reference. Through discussions held with City Power, the following upgrades to the grid are anticipated for this project:                                                                           1. Replacement of existing City Power isolators with Circuit Breakers situated at the Adcock Ingram inlet substation.                                                                                            2. Upgrading of cabling between the Adcock Ingram substation and the Langa feeder substation (addition of a single 185mm 4c cable).                                                                3. Upgrade of the existing Circuit Breakers and other relevant switchgear at Langa substation to be able to accomodate the new generator supply.                                            4. Addition of islanding protection and synchronisation relays to allow for a safe connection between the generator island and the grid upon reconnection of a failed grid supply. ', 'The project will be connected onto the City Power Grid. ', '18', 'The project is in South Africa', '0-30', '47', '30.32', 'Local Contractors will be used for the Civil work; Mechanical Installations and Electrical Installations. Local manufacturers will be used for all power plant scope not included as part of the Wartsila standard product offering. This will include cabling; switchgear; ducting; piping and gas compressors.', '6', 'Spares and components that fall outside the scope of normal supply by the OEM (i.e. Wartsila) will be sourced locally. It is not envisaged, due to the relatively small size of the project, that dedicated component manufacturing facilities and/or training centres will be constructed for this project. However, it should be mentioned that in the event where more facilities such as this appear in South Africa, this would encourage further investment by the OEM in various training and manufacturing facilities for South Africa.', '2013-07-05', '2013-07-12', 'true'),
(89, 268, 'Mitochondria Energy Company (Pty) Ltd', '+27834192837', 'Anthea Bath', 'Brolaz Campus', '223', 'Alexandra Avenue', 'Halfway House', 'Midrand', '1685', 'info@mitochondria.co.za', 'SG Beatrix Mine - MQ.13.07.002B', 'Utilization of the Natural Gas (NG) which is largely Methane that is being expelled from the Beatrix Gold Mine as a result of Sibanye Gold mining activities via a series of boreholes over its development area. Mitochondria is investigating the use of Fuel Cells to convert the NG to electricity from the 6 boreholes and to utilize the heat resultant from this process in the existing boiler for co-generation. Initial estimates will see 8.6 MWe being generated from this source. \r\n\r\nMitochondria Energy Co has been asked to conduct a feasibility study to investigate a potential PPA with the mine utilizing their NG resource as well as the potential of being an IPP to neighbouring communities. Mitochondria Energy Co is looking into possible consolidation of all the outflows into one point and to create additional power to push back into the grid to the neighbouring communities. the mine will likely remain the primary off taker in the interim.\r\n\r\n', 'Other', '', '', '', 'Molten Carbonate Fuel Cell', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '8.6', '1.4', '8.2', '95', '1.00', 'CPI', '47%', '', '', '', 'Quater3', '2015', '18 months from PPA', '2', 'baseload', '12', '345', '23', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', 'Existing off grid; plus exhaust gas around 370 degrees C equivalent to 23,300 MWh per annum and cooling around 10,600 MWh per annum.', '315', '20', '1200', 'TBC', 'CPI', 'yes', '', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', '', '2', '18', 'Mitochondria Energy Company', 'In discussions', 'IDC', 'N/A', 'The Mitochondria Energy Company team has previous experience when in industry (CEO- Anglo Platinum/ Engineering Head - Vodacom)', '0', '0', '0', 'yes', '', '', '', '', 33, 'Terracotta Resources (Pty) Ltd which is 100% BEE and will also include women, youth and  other black owned enti