(90, 57, 'GAS2POWER (G2P)', '+27842192000', 'MARK OTTO', 'G2P', '7', 'Derry Road', 'Greenside East', 'Johannesburg', '2193', 'mark@g2p.co.za', 'GAS2POWER RBIDZ GAS POWERED PEAKER PROJECT', 'The project involves the installation of an IMBEDDED COGENERATION plant at the Richards Bay Industrial Development Zone Phase 1F (RBIDZ). The plant will feed into the uMhlatuze grid within  the RBIDZ zone.The plant can run as a peaking power station.The economic model developed for the MTRM program is based on peaking power.\r\n\r\nGROSS capacity will be 6MW, generated by four x  1.5 MW gas engines powered by methane-rich gas supplied by SPRING LIGHTS GAS. Agreement in principal has been reached with Spring Lights Gas regarding the initial supply of about 280 000 GJ.\r\n\r\nThe four fully containerized Mitsubishi GS 16 R2-PTK gas engines will be installed on site in the RBIDZ. The engines available within 5-6 months and sourced from MITSUBISHI HEAVY INDUSTRIES (MHI) , can be ready for commercial operation within 10 months of  a  PPA being issued. \r\n\r\nThe engines have been secured  between MHI and G2P.\r\nThe site (phase 1F) has been identified and secured within RBIDZ in an MoU.  \r\n\r\nThe site will be developed in phases based on gas availability , PPA''s approved  by the uMhlatuzi municipality in terms of generating as an imbedded generator in the RDIDZ and the securing of PPA''s with the DoE.\r\n\r\nThere are substantial benefits to both the uMhlatuze Municipality and RBIDZ of having Imbedded additional power that can increase in a modular fashion. New investors may now have access to power that was previously unavailable, the municipal grid will receive some relief and several new jobs will be created with associated training opportunities.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Reciprocating', 'Gas', 'ExistingGas', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '6', '1.5', '5.7', '95', '1.2', 'PPI or CPI or linked to fuel price', '41', '', '', '', 'Quater2', '2014', '', '10', 'peaking', '11'