(92, 183, 'Boegoeberg Hydro Electric Power (Pty) Ltd', '+27 21 934 5503', 'Niel Theron', 'Level 3 Terminal Builidng, Execujet Business Centre', '999', 'Tower Road', 'Cape Town International Airport', 'Cape Town', '7525', 'niel@hydro-sa.com', 'Boegoeberg Hydro Electric Project', 'The proposed Boegoeberg Hydro Electric Project would be situated adjacent to the existing Boegoeberg Weir on the Orange River near Groblershoop in the Northern Cape. The project will have an installed capacity of about 10 MW and will supply electricity to the Eskom distribution network.\r\nThe project will divert water around the existing weir into a canal that conveys water to a powerhouse containing two or three Kaplan type turbines. Water will then be returned to the Orange River.\r\nThe hydrology of the Orange River is well understood and is considered to pose little risk to the project. Water comes a no cost to the project.\r\nHydro electric projects are heavily reliant on civil infrastructure and civil works make up a considerable proportion of hte cost of hydro electric projects. Electrical and Mechanical equipment, which generate the electricity, will be sourced from an international supplier.\r\nKey authorisations required for the project include the Environmental Authorisation and the Water Use Licence. Without these authorisations, it will be impossible to construc the project. The Environmental Impact Assessment is underway and should address all the environmental concerns about the project. The environmental asssessment process will be allowed to run its course before a decision is made on whether to proceed with the project.\r\nIt is propsed to bid the Boegeoeberg Hydro Electric Project in Round 4 of REIPP.', 'Hydro', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '10.0', '5', '10.0', '67', '1.06', '5.7%', '', '', '0', '', 'Quater4', '2017', '', '21', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'yes', 'Neusberg Hydro ELectric Project', 'no', '', '350', '20', '1060', '', '5.7%', 'yes', 'Euro, Australian Dollar', 'fastQ2-2013-24Month', '', '6', '21', 'Hydro SA', '', 'Hydro Tasmania South Africa', 'N/A', 'Hydro SA and Hydro Tasmania South Africa are the developers of South Africa''s first run-of-river hydro electric project to be constructed under the REIPP programme. The 10MW Neusberg Hydro Electric Project is currently under construction and is due for completeion in early 2015.Hydro Tasmania is Australia’s leading renewable energy business and the largest manager of water in the country.Hydro Tasmania''s 2,270MW installed capacity is provided by 29 power stations ranging in size from 700 kW to 600MW using water storages in six major catchments. The first of Hydro Tasmania''s major hydro electric projects was constructed in 1914, while the last was completed in 1990. Several small hydros have been iimplemented over the past 15 years. Hydro Tasmania also owns and operates three large scale wind farms with a total installed capacity of over 300 MW.', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 10, 'The Boegoeberg Community Trust will be developed in accordance with requirements of the Implementation Agreement and REIPPP requirements as a minimum. On the Neusberg project we far exceeded most of the requirements set by the Implementation agreement and the REIPP. Accordingly we see no reason why this cannot again be achieved.', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '1', 'no', '', '', '', '', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '1', '', 'draft', 'no', 'Additional geotechnical studies are likely to be required to confirm the geotechnical conditions at the site. No further technical studies are envisaged. Based on it''s experience at the Neusberg Hydro Electric Project, the developer is certain the project will successfully meet the lender''s and equity provider''s financing criteria.', 'Groblershoop, Northern Cape, South Africa', '22', '12', '09', '29', '02', '22', 'no', '', 'no', 'no', '', 'yes', '01/12/2013',