(93, 183, 'Orange Falls Hydro Electric Power (Pty) Ltd', '+27 21 934 5503', 'Niel Theron', 'Level 3 Terminal Building Execuject Business Centre', '999', 'Tower Rd', 'Cape Town International Airport', 'Cape Town', '7525', 'niel@hydro-sa.com', 'Orange Falls Hydro Electric Project', 'The proposed Orange Falls Hydro Electric Project is to be situated near Orange Falls on the Orange River near Velloorsdrif in Namibia. The project will have an installed capacity of about 20 MW and will supply electricity to the NamPower transmission network, or can be used as "Imported Hydro" into South Africa\r\nThe project will divert water from upstream of Orange Falls weir into a canal that conveys water to a powerhouse containing three Kaplan type turbines. Water will then be returned to the Orange River.\r\nThe hydrology of the Orange River is well understood and is considered to pose little risk to the project. Water comes at no cost to the project.\r\nHydro electric projects are heavily reliant on civil infrastructure and civil works make up a considerable proportion of the cost of hydro electric projects. Electrical and Mechanical equipment, which generate the electricity, will be sourced from an international supplier.\r\nKey authorisations required for the project include the Environmental Authorisation and the Water Use Licence. Without these authorisations, it will be impossible to construct the project. The Environmental Impact Assessment is underway and should address all the environmental concerns about the project. The environmental assessment process will be allowed to run its course before a decision is made on whether to proceed with the project.\r\n', 'Hydro', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '20.4', '6.8', '20.4', '55', '1.06', '5.7%', '', '', '0', '', 'Quater2', '2016', '', '21', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '490', '20', '1060', '', '5.7%', 'no', 'Namibian Dollar', 'commitQ2-2014-Phased', '', '6', '21', 'Orange Falls Hydro Electric Power (Pty) Ltd', '', 'Hydro Tasmania South Africa', 'N/A', 'Hydro SA and Hydro Tasmania South Africa are the developers of South Africa''s first run-of-river hydro electric project to be constructed under the REIPP programme. The 10MW Neusberg Hydro Electric Project is currently under construction and is due for completeion in early 2015.Hydro Tasmania is Australia’s leading renewable energy business and the largest manager of water in the country.Hydro Tasmania''s 2,270MW installed capacity is provided by 29 power stations ranging in size from 700 kW to 600MW using water storages in six major catchments. The first of Hydro Tasmania''s major hydro electric projects was constructed in 1914, while the last was completed in 1990. Several small hydros have been iimplemented over the past 15 years. Hydro Tasmania also owns and operates three large scale wind farms with a total installed capacity of over 300 MW.', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 10, 'To be developed in accordance with requirements of the Implementation Agreement and REIPPP requirements as a minimum. On the Neusberg project we far exceeded most of the requirements set by the Implementation Agreement and REIPPP, and see no reason why this cannot again be achieved', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '1', 'no', '', '', '', '', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '0', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '1', '', 'draft', 'no', 'Additional studies are likely to be required to confirm the geotechnical conditions at the site. No further technical studies are envisaged. Based on it''s experience at the Neusberg Hydro Electric Project, the developer is certain the project will successfully meet the lender''s and equity provider''s financing criteria.', 'Velloorsdrif', '19', '14', '54', '28', '50', '13', 'yes', 'The site is owned by the Shareholders of the Project Company', 'no', 'no', '', 'yes', '01/12/2013', '01/06/2014', 'yes', '01/12/2013', '01/07/2014', 'South African approvals will include:•	Notification to responsible heritage resources authority NHRA (s38) - 01/07/2014\r\n•	Heritage Approval(National Heritage Resources Act (Act No. 25 of 1999)) & collection permit to section 35 of the National Heritage Resources Act - 01/07/2014\r\n•	Environmental Authorisation (NEM) - 01/07/2014\r\n•	Biodiversity Consents (NEMBA, NFA, Provincial Nature Conservation Ordinances, and regulations made under them) - 01/07/2014\r\n•	Building Plan Approval (National Building Standards Act) 01/02/2015\r\n•	Water Use Licence / Registration (National Water Act (Act No. 36 of 1998)) - 01/02/2015\r\nNamibian consents are likely to include all those above (the Namibian equivalent thereof, plus: •	Electricity generation licence - 01/02/2015\r\n•	Electricity Distribution licence  - 01/02/2015\r\n•	Grid connection - 01/02/2015\r\n•	Consent to subdivide, or register long lease or servitude, in respect of agricultural land - 01/07/2014.', '62', '19', '42', '25', '28', '23', '00', 'Rock', 'no', '', '', '', 'As we had envisaged that this project was to deliver power purely to Nampower we have not had any discussions with Eskom. In the event that the project could be considered under "imported hydro" we will commence negotiations with Eskom, whom we note have just recently erected a 132KV line to Velloorsdrif (Nam) from South Africa. We believe this line is to be extended to Karasburg in Namibia. In the event that we could supply to this line, we would save in excess of 20km''s transmission.', 'Please see above', 'NamPower or Eskom depending on option availed of (as described above)', '21', 'Please see above', '0-30', '340', '69.39', 'Large steel components such as gates, trashracks, stoplogs and cranes will be manufactured locally.', '150', 'Nil', '2013-07-08', '2013-07-12', 'true');
