(101, 265, 'Mpumi Majavu', '0118672574', 'Mpumi majavu', 'Meyersdal Office Park', '65 ', 'Phillip Engelbrecht Street', 'Meyersdal', 'Alberton', '1448', 'info@brevirite.co.za', 'Nokukhanya Solar Project', 'Nokukhanya Energy as an Independent Power Producer (IPP) is proposing the establishment of a commercial solar energy facility on a site within the Limpopo to be known as Nokukhanya Solar Farm, of size 75MW. The Limpopo is generally known to be one of the preferred areas for the generation of solar energy in South Africa, due to its abundant solar radiation. The purpose of this facility is to generate electricity from a renewable energy source (i.e. solar radiation) to provide power to the national electricity grid. The proposed development site is located within the Groblersdal situated 32 km north, this area lies on the borders of Lumpopo and Mpumalanga Province. It previously was dermacated in the Mpumalanga Province.\r\n\r\nThe applicant is proposing the establishment of a commercial solar energy facility, known as the Nokukhanya Solar Farm and will be operated under the license of acompany bearing the same name, Nokukhanya Solar Farm (Pty) Ltd. The proposed development site is located on a portion of portion 183 of the farm KIKVORSCHFONTEIN No. 57 - JS, which is situated within the jurisdiction of Sekhukhune District Municipality (SDM) was established in december 2000. It consists of five Local Municipalities, namely Elias Motsoaledi, Ephraim Mogale, GreaterTubatse,Fetakgomo, and Makhuduthamaga, in the Limpopo Province. The purpose of the facility is to assist the government in providing much needed\r\nelectricity by generating energy from a renewable energy source-the sun.\r\n\r\nThe proposed facility is to be designed for the generation of approximately 75MW AC (Alternating Current) of electricity, which will be fed into the national electricity grid. The proposed development site covers an area of approximately 65 hectares. The identified 65ha development site is located on a section of the total farm (65, 7984 ha). There are 3 areas where the new platinum mines will be concentrated: The Lebowakgomo District (South). Groblersdal – Cluff mining.The Dilokong or Burgersfort/Steelpoort corridor. The Sekhukhune District recently commissioned an investigation into potential global demand for the key minerals found in its jurisdiction.', 'Other', '', '', '', 'Solar Photovoltaic', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '75', '25', '75', '75', '75', '7', '75', '', '', '', 'Quater4', '2016', '', '24', 'baseload', '12', '365', '24', 'yes', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '85', '20', '2700', '', '7', 'yes', '', 'commitQ2-2016-Phased', '', '6', '24', 'Nokukhanya Energy Group', 'Kayema, Samsung', 'Nokukhanya Energy Group', 'Kayema', 'Kayema is a multi national company in the Middle East and Africa. It was founded in 2005. Brevirite is also a partner with a CIDB level 5 that will assist in Civils', '5000000', '12000000', '8000000', 'no', '', '', '', '', 55, 'Employment of 200 local people will be created during construction. There will be equity holding for the local community', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '1', 'no', '', '', '', '', '', 'no', 'We are in process of finalising the feasibility', 'no', 'We have submitted the application to Department of Environmental Affairs', 'no', 'to be finalized', '2 months after PPA is signed', 'Refer to project plan', 'refer to milestones', '2', 'corporate', '', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '4 ', 'no', 'draft', 'no', 'Detailed studies still to be completed. Desktop studies have been completed. Basic EIA is 95% done', 'Groblersdal, Limpopo, South Africa', '-29', '7', '49.2276', '-25', '15', '42.2064', 'yes', 'Ownership, the transfer of the ownership is in progress. the deed transfer will be finalized in 3 months', 'no', 'yes', '24/07/2012', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'Water License from DWA 4 months,  Bulk Services from Municipality 4 months', '20', '29', '7', '50', '25', '17', '78', 'Kwaggafontein', 'y