(105, 212, 'ISS GLOBAL MINING PTY LTD', '0829051205', 'SIPHO NTULI', 'ARB OFFICE PARK', '34', 'FRICKER ROAD', 'ILLOVO', 'JOHANNESBURG', '2196', 'sntuli@issglobalmining.co.za', 'UMBANI POWER PLANT', ' READINESS STATUS OF THE UMBANI PROJECT\r\n\r\n1. INTRODUCTION\r\nISS Global Mining is a South African Company registered in May 2006. The share holders are Adridini holdings (74%) and Mkhamose Resources (26%) with a R17 Million equity. The company  has been developing the Umbani Project for a number of years and the project has now progressed to an advanced stage. \r\nThe company started developing this project in early 2010 in anticipation of the finalization of the IPP legislation including the IRP. The initial processes involved doing a comprehensive research on the electricity demands of South Africa, then the primary energy source as well as the availability of environmentally acceptable land to bulid a power plant. The research also showed that there is a lot of low grade quality coal still undergroung in South Africa which can not be mined because there is no market for it, even Eskom can not use it. \r\n2. LOCATION \r\nThe planned Power Plant is situated in Mpumalanga Province, on a farm Dorsfontein erf 71 IS, just outside Kriel township in the Gert Sibande district municipality. It is within a 15KM radius with 2 Eskom power stations, namely Kriel and Matla. There  area is surrounded by a lot of coal mines and Eskom’s transmission and distribution networks. It is easily accessible by major roads and railways lines.\r\n3. LAND\r\nThe company has secured 700 hectres  of the farm Dorsfontein 71 IS for the project. An option to buy the land has been signed with the land owner. The land is currently not in use. The company did an environmental assessment of the area to check if it is suitable for a power plant and the study confirmed that it is outside the restricted emission areas of the highveld region.\r\n4. TECHNOLOGY\r\nThe Umbani project is a  500 MW base load coal power plant using a circulating Fluidised Bed (CFB) boilers coupled to subcritical turbo generators. It will be a 2 x 250 MW units. Due to water scarcity in the area, dry cooling will be a better choice for the power plant. The CFB technology burns low quality coal and it is environmentally friendly in terms of gas emmisions compared to the currently used technology in the country. This technology can burn from 8MJ/KG upwards. Although this technology will be new in south Africa, it is very popular and has been used for many decades internationally. It is a proven technology and also  a technology of choice for many countries who still want to use coal and still be compliant with the climate change regulations. The plant emissions will be the lowest of any coal fired plant in Southern Africa and will fully comply with the World Bank and European standards. \r\n5. ENVIRONMENTAL COMPLIANCE\r\nThe company received an approval from the department of environmental  affairs to start with the  Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA) on the area. Currently our environmental specialists are busy with the consultation process as part of the EIA process. The initial environmental study showed that the land is suitable for our power plant and it has the advantage that the plant will be located on the highest point in the area which assists will emissions dispersion. \r\n6. COAL SUPPLY\r\nThe company has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Total Coal SA for the supply of the low grade coal to the power plant. Total Coal S A is one of the big mining companies in South Africa\r\n The mine is called Dorsfontein and it is situated about 1 kilometer from the project site. The coal will be moved by a conveyor belt from the mine to the power plant. The low grade coal has a caloric value of between 13 MJ/KG and 17MJ/KG, the Head Agreeement and Coal Purchase Agreement are ready to be signed pending the outcome of the RFP from the Energy department.Total Coal will be able to supply the coal for the life span of the power plant. Currently samples of the low grade coal from the mine are being tested in a German laboratory which will then enable the equipment designers to tailor the solution to the specific site conditions of Umbani..\r\n7. GRID CONNECTION \r\nThe company applied to Eskom to do the Grid connection study. The studies were concluded and Eskom issued the company with a cost estimate letter confirming that there is infrastructere to connect the power plant to the grid. Pending the start of the procurement  process by the energy department the company will then request a budget letter from Eskom which comes at a cost which will then allow Eskom to finalize the Grid connection study and eventually the connection process.\r\n8. TECHNICAL PARTNERS, EPC, O&M AND IPP \r\nThe company is conducting negotiations with world renowned possible  EPC partners  as well as operator & maintenance (OM) and IPP partners of world class standards.\r\nAlso, pending the start of the procurement process by the Energy Department, contracts will then be finalized with the said partners. \r\n9. FINANCE\r\nFinancing arrangements of the project ( equity and debt ) are at an advanced stage and there are promissory notes  in the form of interest expression from a world class financing institution. The company has finalized the financial model and it is confident that the project is financially viable \r\n10.TIME FRAMES\r\nWe anticipate that it will take between 6 and 12 months to reach financial close after bidder preferred announcement has been made. Construction period will be 32 - 38 months. Commissioning and testing will take a further 8-16 months (for both units). \r\n11. SUMMARY \r\n1.	Land for the power plant -------------- secured (offer to purchase)\r\n2.	Coal supply for the plant -------------- secured  ( MOU & HOA)\r\n3.	Grid connection of the plant-----------confirmed (cost estimate letter)\r\n4.	Technology of choice      ---------------finalized  (lab test for boiler design)\r\n5.	EPC partner                    ---------------identified (with expression of interest )\r\n6.	OM partner                     --------------- identified (with expression of interest)\r\n7.	Financial partner            ----------------identified (with expression of interest)\r\n8.      IPP Partner                   ---------------- secured  \r\n\r\n12. CONCLUSION\r\nThe company believes that all the above is evidence that the project is at an advanced stage and it is ready for implementation.  We are now waiting for the Department of Energy (DoE ) to issue the Request for Proposal or alternatively immediately engage in negotiations with DoE in order to initiate all the above processes. We firmly believe that once the preferred bidder is announced, we will be generating electricity within 60 months. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n.\r\n', 'Thermal', 'Coal', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '550', '250', '500', '87', '1.15', 'CPI', '37%', '', '', '', 'Quater2', '2019', '', '60', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '20000', '25', '1150', '6% annual escalation', 'CPI', 'yes', '', 'commitQ3-2013-Phased', '', '6', '60', 'ISS Global Mining (Pty) Ltd', 'Commercially confidential', 'Commercially confidential', 'Commercially confidential', 'ISS, its shareholders and employees have participated in a number of power project developments in Africa. ISS is at a critical stage with negotiations with a number of International Developer partners we expect to nominate the developer partner within the next few weeks.', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 26, 'TBA', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '', 'no', '6', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', '02/07/2019', 'no', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '6', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '6', '', 'draft', 'yes', 'Fuel resource already in production', 'Kriel, Mpumalanga, Gert Sibande District Municipality.', '29', '20', '04.74', '26', '13', '18.57', 'yes', 'Draft land sale agreement with current landowner in place. currently the company has been given permission to do all studies on the site. depending on the outcome of the RFP,a land purchase agreement will be signed.', 'yes', 'yes', '03/10/2011', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'In addition to the Record of Decision from the DEA, the following permits and licenses will have to be obtained, however these are considered to be a relative formality:\r\n•	Building\r\n•	Air Emissions\r\n•	Water\r\n•	Abnormal Loads\r\n•	DMR Borrow pits\r\n•	SAHRA\r\n•	Plant Disturbance\r\n•	Generating License\r\n•	Grid Connection License\r\n', '3', '29', '20', '19.15', '26', '12', '59.93', 'Main 400 kV transmission line at northern end of property', 'yes', '06/10/2011', 'yes', '31 January 2012\r\nRef: 60047933 Helen Bezuidenhout\r\n2000 MW Umbani\r\n', 'Various meetings held with Eskom Grid Division in 2011, 2012 and 2013. Proposal received from Eskom in January 2012 as per above. Revised application (for 500 MW) submitted in May 2013. ', 'Awaiting Eskom final confirmation, however the preferred solution is to directly the join the existing 400 kV line which crosses the northern boundary of the property.', 'Eskom', '48', 'Not applicable', '65-75', '10000', '50.00', 'Due to the high local content requirements and to mitigate against Rand volatility during the construction period the project will have a significant local content of approximately 50%. We anticipate that a substantial portion of the boiler, turbo alternator, mechanical plant, electrics and instrumentation will be manufactured in South Africa and that this manufacturing will have an approximate value of R 4 000 m. We believe that this will support many thousands of jobs in the industrial manufacturing industries in South Africa.', '300', 'The construction period of the project will extend over a 4 year period. We anticipate that during peak construction activities, over 1200 persons will be involved in on site construction activities with the majority of these workers coming from the surrounding local areas of Mpumalanga and eastern Gauteng. The timing of the project is such that as resources are demobilized from the nearby Kusile project they will then be ultilised on the Umbani project, providing a continuity of employment and retention of skills in the region built up over the preceding 5 years. ', '2013-07-08', '2013-07-11', 'true'),
(106, 148, 'Illovo Sugar (South Africa) Limited', '0315084550', 'Warren Wessels', 'Building 3C, Gleneagles Park', '10', 'Flanders Drive', 'Mount Edgecombe', 'Durban', '4300', 'wwessels@illovo.co.za', 'Umzimkulu Small Project (optimisation)', 'The Umzimkulu Mill currently generates its own power requirements by burning bagasse in its low pressure boilers. Illovo has undertaken a study of the feasibility of optimising back-pressure power generation from existing steam generation capacity and fuel supply. The factory currently operates with a letdown margin and has inefficient steam turbine drives which would be replaced with electric motors. Marginal improvements will be made to steam economy to achieve a bagasse only fuel balance.\r\nTo secure cane supplies for the period of the PPA it is necessary to enter into long term cane supply agreements with the farmers. The farmers will require remuneration for this long term commitment.\r\nAs this is an optimisation process within the existing business it will be corporate finaced and there will be no change to Illovo South Africa''s BBBEE flowing directly from it. It should be noted that once the outstanding Lands Claims have been settled, black farmers will supply well over 50% of Illovo''s cane supply and the additional revenue source will be important in supporting the viability of the farming community. \r\nNote if required the project could be phased with 3MW coming on stream in April 2015 and the full 7MW in April 2016.', 'Cogeneration', 'Integrated', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '27', '15', '7', '69', '1.28', 'CPI', '', '71', '', '', 'Quater2', '2016', 'To achieve the planned timetable requires the signature of the PPA by 1 June 2014, which in turn requires the receipt of a bankable PPA by 1 September 2013', '22', 'mid-merit', '8', '240', '24', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '170', '10', '1280', 'The tariff of R 1280 is based on 1- April- 2011 terms. The tariff based on 1 -April- 2013 would be R1430', 'CPI', 'yes', '', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', 'To achieve the stated COD a Bankable PPA is required by 1 September 2013 in order to sign the PPA by 1 June 2014', '7', '22', 'Illovo Sugar (South Africa) Limited', 'Illovo Sugar Limited', 'not applicable', 'not applicable', 'Respondent operates 4 electricity and steam generating operations in South Africa with an installed capacity of 56 MW. Illovo Sugar Limited, the parent company and technology provider, operates a further 120 MW of installed capacity in the rest of Africa. This includes a recently installed 25MW plant in Swaziland which delivers power to the grid.', '4078700000', '3030200000', '3115000000', 'yes', '', '', '', '', 14, 'As this project is an optimisation within the scope of the existing business, no new community involvement is planned beyond the various devlopment initiatives already in existance.\r\n\r\nNote the 14% BEE participation shown in the above box reflects Illovo Sugar Limited''s  participation in BBBEE Contributor Status scorecard.', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '9', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '9', 'corporate', '', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '9', '', 'finalised', 'yes', 'As a corporate financed project within the normal scope of business it does not require any studies.', 'Port Shepstone', 'E 30', '25', '18', 'S 30', '43', '30', 'yes', 'ownership', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'Optimisation project that can be undertaken within the bounds of existing authorisations.', '1', 'E 30', '25', '18', 'S 30 ', '43 ', '30', 'Eskom Shepstone Sub-station', 'yes', '27/05/2013', 'yes', 'Ref IPP 72437578', 'Discussed co-generation with Mr. Ravi Moonsamy of Eskom and the need to connect to the grid via an overhead line. ', 'Upgrade required to connect to the grid via an overhead line. A new transformer, generator control and protection is required.', 'Eskom grid', '12', 'N/A', '55-65', '120', '63.83', 'Turbine imported, but piping and fitments sourced locally', '5', 'N/A', '2013-07-08', '2013-07-11', 'true'),
(107, 212, 'ISS GLOBAL MINING PTY LTD', '0829051205', 'SIPHO NTULI', 'ARB OFFICE PARK', '34', 'FRICKER ROAD', 'ILLOVO', 'JOHANNESBURG', '2196', 'sntuli@issglobalmining.co.za', 'ELOFF POWER PLANT', 'STATUS OF THE ELOFF POWER   PROJECT\r\n\r\n1. INTRODUCTION\r\nISS Global Mining (Iss Gm) is a South African Company registered in May 2006. The share holders are Adridini holdings (74%) and Mkhamose Resources (26%) with a R17 Million equity. The company  has been developing both the Umbani and the Eloff Project for a number of years and the projects have now progressed to  advanced stages. Both projects have the same partners ( coal supply,technical & financial)  \r\nThe company started developing this project in early 2010 in anticipation of the finalization of the IPP legislation including the IRP. The initial processes involved doing a comprehensive research on the electricity demands of South Africa, then the primary energy source as well as the availability of environmentally acceptable land to bulid a power plant. The research also showed that there is a lot of low grade quality coal still undergroung in South Africa which can not be mined because there is no market for it, even Eskom can not use it. \r\n2. LOCATION \r\nThe planned Power Plant is situated in Mpumalanga Province, on a farm ELOFF, just outside Delmas township in the Nkangala district municipality. The area is surrounded by a lot of coal mines and Eskom’s transmission and distribution networks. It is easily accessible by major roads and railways lines.\r\n3. LAND\r\nThe farm Eloff is 7500 hectares in size and is owned a  mining company that have mining rights over it.Total Coal South Africa (TCSA) is the majority shareholder and the operator in the mining company. Iss Gm  has negotiated with Total Coal South Africa (TCSA) to buy 700 hactres of  the Eloff farm for a power plant and TCSA has agreed to sell such a portion. The formal procedure will commence immediately after the announcement of RFP by the Energy department.\r\n4. TECHNOLOGY\r\nThe Eloff  project is a mirror image of the Umbani project. It is a 500 MW base load coal power plant using a circulating Fluidised Bed (CFB) boilers coupled to subcritical turbo generators. It will be a 2 x 250 MW units. Due to water scarcity in the area, dry cooling will be a better choice for the power plant. The CFB technology burns low quality coal and it is environmentally friendly in terms of gas emmisions compared to the currently used technology in the country. This technology can burn from 8MJ/KG upwards. Although this technology will be new in south Africa, it is very popular and has been used for many decades internationally. It is a proven technology and also  a technology of choice for many countries who still wants to use coal and still be compliant with the climate change regulations. The plant emmissions will be the lowest in Southern africa and will fully comply with the World Bank and European standards. The company has concluded initial agreements with the company that owns such a technology and also produces high quality CFB technology boilers (Doosan-Lentjies GMBH, Germany\r\n5. ENVIRONMENTAL COMPLIANCE\r\nThe company is currently doing an environmental assesment to check if the land falls outside the emmission area. The land is about 70KM from an existing Eskom power station and about 60KM from an industrialized area with possible gas emmissions. The company is confident that the site will be environmentally suitable for a power plant. \r\n6. COAL SUPPLY\r\nTCSA has agreed to supply the Eloff Power plant with low grade coal from the Eloff mine. The mine is currently not in operation and TCSA has just finalized a feasibility study, aplied for a mining license from the Department of Mineral Resources. It is expected that it will take about 12 months to have the mining license approved. \r\n The plant will be situated on the same farm with the mine. The coal will be moved by a conveyor belt from the mine to the power plant. The low grade coal has a caloric value of between 13 MJ/KG and 17MJ/KG, the Head Agreeement and Coal Purchase Agreement are ready to be signed pending the outcome of the RFP from the Energy department.Total Coal will be able to supply the coal for the life span of the power plant. Currently samples of the low grade coal from the mine are being tested in a German labolatory which will then enable the engineers to do a proper boiler design.\r\n7. GRID CONNECTION \r\nThere is 132 Kva Eskom line passing through the Eloff farm.The company is in a process of applying to Eskom to do the Grid connection study. Preliminary discussions with Eskom shows that grid connection of the Eloff power plant is definite possible. \r\n8. TECHNICAL PARTNERS, EPC, O&M AND IPP\r\nThe company has concluded negotiations with world reknown possible  EPC partners as well as operator & maintenance (OM) and IPP partners of world class standards.\r\nBoth companies are very reputable and has a huge experience in such a projects.\r\nAlso, pending the start of the procurement process by the Energy Department, contracts will then be finalized with the said partners. The above mentioned technical partners have already engaged and identified suitable equipment suppliers as well as done some costings of it. They have also identified local companies who will give the whole project a local content in terms of product and services supply.\r\n9. FINANCE\r\nFinancing arrangements of the project ( equity and debt ) are at an advanced stages and there are promisory notes  in the form of interest expression from a world class financing institution. The company is busy doing a financial model for the Eloff power Plant. \r\n10.TIME FRAMES\r\nWe anticipate that mining in Elloff will only commence in 2017. It will take 12 months to reach financial close after bidder preferred announcement has been made. Construction period will take 42 - 48 months. Commission and testing another 6-8 months for both units. \r\n11. SUMMARY \r\n1.	Land for the power plant -------------- secured (agreed in principle )\r\n2.	Coal supply for the plant -------------- secured  ( agreed in principle)\r\n3.	Grid connection of the plant----------- application to be submitted to Eskom\r\n4.	Technology of choice      ---------------finalized  (lab test for boiler design)\r\n5.	EPC partner                    ---------------identified (with expression of interest )\r\n6.	OM partner                     --------------- identified (with expression of interest)\r\n7.	Financial partner            ----------------identified (with expression of interest)\r\n8.     IPP Partner                    ----------------secured                             \r\n\r\n\r\n12. CONCLUSION\r\nThe company believes that all the above proves that the project will be ready once mining has begun in Eloff.  We are now awaiting for the Department of Energy ( DoE ) to issue the Request for Proposal or alternatively enter into negotiations with the DoE on this project, we can put all the above processes into action. We firmly beleave that once the preferred bidder is announced, it will take 72 months and the power plant will start supplying the 500MW into the national grid. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n.\r\n', 'Thermal', 'Coal', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '550', '250', '500', '87', '1.15', 'CPI', '37', '', '', '', 'Quater4', '2020', '', '72', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '20000', '25', '1150', '6% annual escalation', 'CPI', 'yes', '', 'commitQ3-2013-Phased', '', '6', '72', 'ISS Global Mining (Pty) Ltd', 'Commercially Confidential', 'Commercially Confidential', 'Commercially Confidential', 'ISS, its shareholders and employees have participated in a number of power project developments in Africa. ISS is at a critical stage with negotiations with a number of international developer partners. We expect to nominate the developer partner within the next few weeks.', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 26, 'TBA', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', 'no', 'no', '12 ', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '09/07/2013', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', '', 'no', '', '36 months after signature of the  Bankable PPA', 'NOT APPLICABLE', 'NOT APPLICABLE', '36', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '12', 'yes', 'draft', 'yes', 'all studies needed for the mining of the resources has been completed. The fuel supplier has applied for a mining right from the mineral Resources department.', 'Delmas town, Nkangala district municipality, Mpumalanga province', '28', '30', '560', '26', '16', '050', 'yes', 'The fuel supplier is the owner of the site and has agreed in principle to sell 700 hectares of land to ISS GM for the power plant', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'environmental EIA, emission, water use license                                                                         it will take 12 months to get the licenses', '3', '28', '45', '045', '26', '16', '00', 'not applicable at the moment', 'no', '', '', '', 'informally Eskom has indicated that it looks possible to connect the power plant into the grid. there is a transmission line running through the site', 'there is a transmission line running through the property', 'ESKOM', '48', 'not applicable', '65-75', '10000', '50.00', 'Due to the high local content requirements and to mitigate against Rand volatility during construction period, the project will have significant local content of approximately 50%. we anticipate that a substantial portion of the boilers, turbo alternator, mechanical plant, electrics and instrumentation will be manufactures in south africa', '300', 'The construction period of the project will extend over a 4 year period. we anticipate that during the peak construction period, over 1200 jobs will be created. the labour will be drawn from the local surrounding communities. the project is not far from the current Kusile power station, so there will be skills that will be utilized that would