(111, 186, 'Dundee Biogas Power (Pty) Ltd', '0861004637', 'Johannes Wolmarans', 'Solek & Bathrooms4U', '15', 'George Blake', 'Plankenbrug', 'Stellenbosch', '7599', 'johannes@solek.co.za', 'Dundee Biogas Power (Pty) Ltd', 'The project involves a typical bio-gas plant as currently under development by Solek (Renewable Energy Engineers). The client in this specific case runs a feedlot which constitutes primary waste or raw-material supplied to the bio-digester. The potential for power generation, waste management and fertiliser production were the main drivers behind the project.\r\n\r\nProject feasibility is mainly based on income earned from energy fed into the national grid at the renewable energy feed-In tariff as provided by NERSA. Secondly, carbon credits will generate another income stream. Furthermore, aims are to assist in the development of domestic renewable energy technology and skills and promote a low-carbon energy industry.\r\n\r\nThe process involves the supply of animal manure into an anaerobic bio-digester which produces bio-gas (methane) for combustion in a power generating engine. Raw material (manure & waste) throughput is calculated at 75 kiloton per annum.\r\n\r\nThe waste product after digestion is inert and may be used for fertiliser production or used on pasture lands as fertiliser. \r\n', 'Reciprocating', 'Gas', 'other33', '', '', '', '', '', 'Biogas (similar to natural gas)', '', '', '', '1.5', '1.5', '1.5', '95', '1.00', 'CPI increase', '', '', '', '', 'Quater3', '2015', 'Construction period is 2-3 months, main issue is manufacturing lead times of equipment. ', '15', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '75', '20', '50000000', '', 'n/a', 'yes', '', 'commitQ2-2014-Phased', '', '8', '18', 'Solek', 'Weltec BioPower', 'n/a', 'n/a', 'In 2011, WELTEC BIOPOWER GmbH, one of the first manufacturers of biogas plants, celebrated its 10th anniversary. WELTEC is one of the pioneers of the constructors of biogas plants. Based on the modern approach of experienced engineers, the company from Vechta, Germany with its expertise of a staff of over 80, offers complete biogas plants from one source and has developed to a leading constructor of biogas plants in the world. \r\nWELTEC BIOPOWER plans and produces complete biogas plants made from stainless steel and distributes them world-wide. WELTEC has realised more than 250 plants all over Europe the United States and even on Cyprus, in China and in Japan. \r\nTo further build on this success WELTEC BIOPOWER has established subsidiaries that should handle customer requirements on a local level in several countries like England, US and other Eastern European countries.', '5000000', '5000000', '5000000', 'no', '', '', '', '', 5, 'Solek, as project developer, sees itself as a contributor to people and their community. The needs and requirements of the people and industry in the province and area are vital to the continued improvement of the province and the country as a whole. \r\n\r\nAs the renewable energy industry is a very young industry, the key social development factors and contributions can be seen in the knowledge transfer and skills development that the project brings to the table within Dundee area and the greater KwaZulu-Natal province. Consulting firms, municipalities, agricultural sector and local people are met with exposure to this “new” technology in South Africa and the possibilities it brings to the province. \r\n\r\nAll of the farm workers, farmers and other community players is exposed to this new industry and the potential thereof through this project. The contribution in terms of exposure and knowledge transfer cannot be expressed in monetary value.  The project equips and localises consultants and players in this field with background and knowledge on this industry. This is extensively portrayed in the previous section where it was highlighted the vast input that is required from various fields of expertise. \r\n', 'yes', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '', 'no', '3', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', '01/09/2013', 'yes', '01/09/2013', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', 'project', '', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '6', '', 'finalised', 'no', 'Yes, all completed. ', 'Dundee, KZN', '30', '21', '30.64', '28', '07', '12.73', 'yes', 'All have already been secured, e.g. road access, water, manure supply, electricity, land, slurry off-take, etc. ', 'yes', 'yes', '', 'no', '', '12/07/2013', 'no', '', '', 'None other than registration of notarial lease and building plans approvals, all will take 2-3 months to complete. Also IPP generation license from NERSA after PPA approval. ', '0.1', '30', '21', '30.64', '28', '07', '12.73', 'Dundee 88/11kV Substation, Network Breaker 19 (DND 19)', 'yes', '30/06/2010', 'yes', 'Cost estimate has been obtained for 1.1 MVA, although the plant could go up to 2 MVA. Connection cost was estimated by Eskom at R4M. ', 'All work has been done through Ravi Moonsamy, Eastern Region, KZN. The project has been registered, also an application was lodged for power supply to the plant. Over the last 2-3 years several engagements have taken place. We have all the support we need from the Eastern Region and they await our next steps to kick-off their processes. No issues have prevailed thus far from Eskom''s side. ', 'None whatsoever, only a small substation and switchgear will have to be installed onsite next to the connection point on the local distribution network. ', 'Eskom', '12', 'South Africa', '65-75', '20', '20.00', 'Electrical equipment and civil works. ', '3', 'The technology provider will have to open an office in South Africa. As the renewable energy industry is a very young industry, the key social development factors and contributions can be seen in the knowledge transfer and skills development that the project brings to the table within Dundee area and the greater KwaZulu-Natal province. Consulting firms, municipalities, agricultural sector and local people are met with exposure to this “new” technology in South Africa and the possibilities it brings to the province. All of the farm workers, farmers and other community players is exposed to this new industry and the potential thereof through this project. A training centre can be established for schools and technology universities. ', '2013-07-09', '2013-07-12', 'true');
