(130, 276, 'HyGen Group (PTY) LTD', '+27826818016', 'Shane Verster', 'N/A', '48', 'Wimbledon Way', 'Edgemead', 'Cape Town', '7441', 'shaneverster@hygengroup.co.za', 'Fish River Community Project - Adamsfontein POC', 'Overview\r\nElectrical supply and stability within the Cradock region is inconsistent. Along the Great Brak and Great Fish rivers, there are several points where small scale hydroelectric units can be installed.\r\nThis project requires the installation of generation equipment to an existing weir located on the Great Brak River approximately 2Km downstream from the Grassridge Dam, in the Eastern Cape. Water supply from the Great Brak River will be passed through the machines to generate power to the grid. The existing weir will create a hydraulic head allowing the generation of renewable electrical power.\r\nAdditionally, a second site will be built 3Km downstream from the first site on the Great Brak River and will require a new 2.5m weir to be constructed. The water will then be piped 150m down the side of the river and then transferred through the generation equipment back into the river.\r\nAt the sites, all relevant control and protection gear will be supplied ensuring that current legislation and standards are met.\r\nThe electrical power will be distributed to the grid via a POC (Point of Coupling) to the utility. The POC will be located approximately 1.5Km upstream from the second site and will be located adjacent to an Eskom supply. At this point the power, via the turbines and the distribution system, will be controlled and metered. The Eskom Interconnection Standard has been adopted within the design and feasibility study.\r\nThe turbine component will be sourced from abroad. All further related equipment and materials will be sourced locally and will be outsourced to local consultants and contractors to design, procure and contract manage (EPCM).\r\nHyGen group will then operate and maintain the machinery for the duration of the PPA based on our knowledge relating to hydroelectric power and managing a PPA with a Utility.\r\nIt is envisaged that the sites will generate the following electrical power and energy per annum through the POC to the utility:\r\n•	Site A:	1.1MW\r\n•	Site B:	1.2MW\r\n•	Total:	2.3MW and 6.147GWh per annum\r\n\r\nFuel Supply (arrangements)\r\nThe “fuel” source will be water which is supplied from the Grassridge dam. This supply is consistently supplied throughout the year except within June when, between ten (10) to twenty (20) days of the year, there is a river shut to perform annual maintenance. Water will not be “used” during the process as is the case for irrigation. Instead, the potential energy within the water source transferred to electrical energy through the turbines and then discharged back into the river in order to harness the power.\r\n\r\nMain cost drivers for project.\r\nSite A\r\n1.	Civils – R2M\r\n2.	Turbine and ancillaries – R9M\r\n3.	Electrical distribution, protection and control – R3.4M\r\nSite B\r\n1.	Civils – R3.5M\r\n2.	Turbine and ancillaries – R9M\r\n3.	Electrical distribution, protection and control – R3M\r\nPOC\r\n1.	Civils – R0.5M\r\n2.	Electrical distribution, protection and control – R1M\r\nProfessional Fees\r\n1.	Principle Consultant and Project Management– R2.2M\r\n2.	Civils and Mechanical- R2.7M\r\n3.	Electrical and Instrumentation- R1M\r\nTotal Project Cost R37.3M\r\n\r\nDecision points to proceed. (Please refer to attached Gantt for more detail)\r\n1.	Application as a preferred bidder with the DoE.\r\n2.	Application for a generation licence with NERSA.\r\n3.	Application to DWA for water licence.\r\n4.	Application to Eskom to connect to Grid.\r\n5.	Securing a PPA.\r\n6.	Approval of funding from financiers.\r\n7.	Appointment of Principle contractor to project.\r\n8.	Design and procurement of Equipment.\r\n9.	Construction and Installation completion.\r\n10.	Commissioning.\r\n11.	COD.\r\n\r\nUnusual features\r\nAll items, except the electrical overhead lines, within this project will be positioned so as to limit the aesthetic layout of the land. \r\nTiming of weir, forebay and tailrace development is critical as the river is shut once a year during June for between 20 to 30 days. During this time all works related to civil works adjacent or on the river will need to take place. That would include any temporary break waters or diverting.\r\n', 'Hydro', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2.5', '1.3', '1.8', '80', '.85', 'NA', '', '', 'N/A', '', 'Quater4', '2015', 'None', '24', 'none', '11', '30', '24', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '37.3', '15', '880.00', '', '0', 'yes', '', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', '', '3', '26', 'HyGen Group (PTY) Ltd', 'Turbine and components short listed to three suppliers from Germany, India and China.', 'None', 'None', 'We are a new company and the experience has been within working environments outside of the business. The designer has been part of the design team for a new 25MW steam turbine for past employment in Swaziland and also designed, procured, project managed, commissioned and managed the installation of a 1.5MW hydroelectric system in Swaziland.\r\nWithin the team we have experience in running a 43MW (combined) steam and hydroelectric “generator” managing the PPA with SEC in Swaziland.\r\n', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 30, 'Houses used to facilitate the construction work force will be reused to on the farmlands and within the community once the project has been completed. Local contractors and workforce will be used as far as reasonably practicable to construct and supply materials for the project.', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '3', 'no', '', '', '', '', '', 'no', 'Communications with DWA are underway for water usage licence.', 'no', 'EIA has been contacted with a preliminary visit.', 'no', 'Civils to take place in project for water control', 'Water availible', 'Please see attached Gantt', 'Please see attached Gantt', '3', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '3', 'no', 'draft', 'no', 'Most have been completed but need to be verified by a third party. CSIR have been approached to do so.', 'Cradock, Eastern Cape, South Africa', '31', '46', '41.66', '25', '25', '19.93', 'yes', 'Agreement in princple with Landowners', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '11/07/2013', 'no', '', '', 'DWA for water usage\r\nNersa for generation licence\r\nZoning Application\r\n', '2', '31', '47', '27.23', '25', '26', '18.83', 'Unknown', 'no', '', '', '', 'Have had contact with Regional Engineer to establish routes and POC point in the region.', 'No transmission line, however, the protection on the line will need to be upgraded.', 'Eskom', '8', 'N/A', '40-45', '19', '50.94', 'Civil works, Housing, Electrical Infrastructure and Design', '50', 'BBEEE in house Engineer in Training and maintenance development within the region.', '2013-07-10', '2013-07-11', 'true'),
(131, 102, 'Aldworth Mbalati', '0126650662', 'Andries Van Tonder', 'Building 11, Cambridge Office Park', '5', 'Bauhinia Street', 'Highveld Techno Park', 'Centurion', '0169', 'andries@adcprojects.com', 'Highveld CCGT Project', '1200MW - Highveld CCGT Project \r\n\r\nAfrican International Energy has formed a partnership with NT Energy which envisages developing the Highveld and Tully Coal-bed Methane (CBM) gas fields in the Amersfoort and Volksrust areas. This partnership will allow for a long term fuel supply agreement to be signed between the Combined Cycle Gas Turbine (CCGT) power plant and the gas field developer. The agreement will facilitate the establishment of the Highveld CCGT Project and in turn guarantee the availability of the generated power capacity.\r\n\r\nMajuba Power Station is located within this gas field area and the developers have identified a location within the Eskom free title zone (Eskom allocated area) and propose to construct the CCGT power plant on this allocated location. Site Coordinates are as follows: 27° 8.849''S 29° 44.865''E \r\n\r\nThe CCGT plant will be constructed over a 3 year period utilising a modular design approach to allow for the full development of the gas field over time.  Preliminary gas tests from test wells have indicated that at least 1600 MW of power could be generated from the above mentioned two gas fields.\r\n\r\nBy applying a modular design approach, stages of 5 x 251 MW will be implemented to ensure power availability from year 1 in parallel with the gas field development process.\r\n\r\nA 400kV step-up transformer will be installed and a switch yard be constructed within the vicinity of the CCGT plant. This will allow the project to utilise the transmission network already established by Majuba power station for the export of electricity onto the Eskom grid. Eskom’s Grid Access Unit has already been approached to address grid connection requirements.\r\n', 'GasPlant', 'CCGT', 'other31', '', '', '', '', 'Coal Bed Methane', '', '', '', '', '1380', '251', '1255', '80', '0.8144', '6.5%', '52.5', '', '', '', 'Quater2', '2016', '', '36', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'yes', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '28700', '30', '860', '', '6.5%', 'yes', '', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', '', '6', '36', 'African International Energy', 'Siemens', 'ADC Projects', 'Siemens', 'Siemens - Profile Attached; ADC Projects - Profile Attached', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 70, 'Community upliftment projects for the communities of Amersfoort and Volksrust.', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '', 'no', '3', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', '30/06/2016', 'yes', '30/06/2016', 'no', '', 'no', '•	The gas reserve currently in place is 750 BCF (12 years gas supply).\r\n•	Only the biggest coal seam was measured - no measurement on shales and other       seams.\r\n•	It is expected that once a resource statement is issued we will have 2.5 TCF of recoverable gas, based on drill results.\r\n•	Resource statement should be available in approximately 6 months. \r\n•	160 Coal seam wells and 12 gas wells have been drilled.\r\n•	Work still to be done include 6 more wells and spot drilling; desorption, adsorption and flow water for final feasibility.\r\n•	Pre-feasibility and a worst case gas price is assumed.\r\n', 'no', '•	Production wells will be constructed in alignment with the work program as scheduled for power production.\r\n•	Application for the production rights is currently being prepared.\r\n', '18 months', 'Refer to schedule 01 (attached)', 'Refer to schedule 01 (attached)', '6', 'project', '', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '12', 'yes', 'draft', 'yes', 'Studies have not been completed and additional studies might be required. (Current gas field and test well data attached)', 'Majuba Power Station, Volksrust, Mpumalanga', '29', '44', '51.90', '27', '8', '50.94', 'yes', 'Eskom land disposal', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', '•       Production Right Application - CBM Gas: 	 12 months\r\n•	Grid Access Application: 		                 12 months \r\n•	Generation license: 		                         12 months\r\n•	Water use license: 		                           8 months\r\n•	Waste Disposal License Enquiry: 	           1 month\r\n•	Emissions license: 		                          12 months\r\n', '3.5', '29', '45', '59.11', '27', '7', '14.88', 'Majuba Power Station', 'no', '11/07/2013', '', '', '•	Discussions with the Eskom Properties Division indicated that Eskom would be willing to allocate land to the project which will be utilised for the power plant and the switch yard.  \r\n•	Discussions with the Eskom Grid Access Unit has also commenced and the application to access the network is being drafted.\r\n', 'A new transmission line from the Highveld CCGT Project to a new 400kV switch yard at coordinates indicated above and a new connection point to the current 400kV network around Majuba Power Station is envisaged.', 'Only to Eskom.', '18', 'The project is located inside South Africa.', '75-85', '7175', '25.00', 'Piping, Civils, Transmission line infrastructure.', '1000', '•	For the chosen technology, we do not see a local opportunity for component manufacturing.\r\n•	The project envisages establishing an artisan-training center as part of the long-term operation and maintenance activity.\r\n', '2013-07-10', '2013-07-12', 'true'),
(132, 224, 'Bamboo Innovations Africa (Pty) Ltd', '0727663955', 'Pelo Gabaraane', 'Unit F', '1 ', 'Lancaster Place', 'Vincent', 'East London', '5247', 'pelo@sabamboo.com', 'Bamboo Energy', 'The project intends establishing separate biomass to energy clusters in rural areas of South Africa, starting in the Eastern Cape Province. A single biofuel production cluster, which will require 1 500 hectares of fallow, degraded or marginal land for biomass feedstock development, is planned for each local municipality, starting with the Great Kei Local Municipality of the Amathole District in the Eastern Cape. \r\n\r\nEach local cluster intends planting and growing giant non-invasive bamboo to produce 60 000 tons of renewable biomass feedstock per year, to be utilised by a local biofuel plant located within the same cluster, with a capacity to produce 3 MW of electricity, one million litres of biodiesel and 5 000 tons of biocoal. \r\n\r\nEach cluster is intended to produce locally and meet the energy demands of the local municipality it is located in.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n', 'Reciprocating', 'Diesel', 'LiquidFuelOther', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Liquid fuel will be produced by onsite conversion of bamboo feedstock into biodiesel', '', '', '3', '3', '3', '85', '0.8', '8.5', '', '', '', '', 'Quater1', '2015', '', '3', 'none', '12', '365', '24', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '200', '20', '1.18', '', '6.5', 'yes', '', 'commitQ2-2014-Phased', '', '3', '3', 'Bamboo Innovations Africa (Pty) Ltd', '', 'The Biomass Corporation SA (Pty) Ltd', 'GPH GmbH', 'None is South Africa.', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 60, 'Rural communities will be involved in feedstock development through local cooperatives. The cooperatives will grow, harvest and sell bamboo feedstock to the biofuel plants and also take equity positions in biofuel production and electricity generation.', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', '3', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', 'Feasibility study is in progress.'