(149, 368, 'Gigawatt Mozambique, SA', '+27 12 682 9120', 'Johan de Vos', 'Gigawatt Office', '222', 'Rua Lucas Elias Kumato', 'Sommerschield', 'Maputo', '1000', 'nwilkens@gigajoule.co.za', 'Gigawatt Mozambique, SA', 'Gigawatt submitted a response to the original RFI on 26 March 2012. In addition Gigawatt submitted a full set of due diligence documentation to the DOE in December of the same year. We refer you to the above two submissions as well as our further letter and submission dated 22 April 2012.\r\n\r\nSince our letter of 22 April 2013 no significant progress was made in finalising a PPA with the DOE and we were subsequently not able to satisfy the request from the Minister of Energy in Mozambique to provide him with a firm schedule for the construction of the permanent power station before the end of April 2013. \r\nIn conjunction with this, the growing demand for electricity in Mozambique led the Minister to issue a further dispatch, stipulating that all power generated from natural gas in Mozambique, should first be utilized to meet the demand within Mozambique and that any surplus power so generated may be sold to third parties.\r\n\r\nIn as far as it is necessary, we would like to iterate that our submission to the DOE in response to the RFI of June 2012 is hereby repeated in response to your RFRI of June 2013 for any surplus power generated at the Gigawatt 100 MW Power Plant at Ressano Garcia.  All documentation and information submitted to the DOE, ESKOM and the IPP team since March 2012 is still applicable and may be considered in response to your RFRI of June 2013.\r\n\r\nPlease note that Gigawatt offered numerous options in relation to the configuration of the plant in its submissions. These are all detailed in the detailed submissions. \r\nUnfortunately the field inputs of this online form do not make it possible to capture these various configurations and as such Gigawatt refers the DOE to these submissions instead. Consequently Gigawatt submits a v