(154, 70, 'BR Energy Ubu Investment Holdings JV', '0833990283', 'Ian Curry', 'Level 1', '30 ', 'Melrose Boulevard', 'Melrose Arch', 'Johannesburg', '2076', 'icurry@brenergy.co.za', 'Rosslyn CHP Plant', 'The proposed Rosslyn Combined Heat and Power Plant is being developed in conjunction with certain motor vehicle manufacturers to supply their industrial heat and electrical requirements. \r\n\r\nThe CHP plant will run on Liquid Natural Gas supplied by Sasol and will generate between 15 - 25 MW of electrical power.\r\n\r\nThe project pre-feasibility study has been completed and shows that the project is technically feasible without having to upgrade any of the installed gas infrastructure in the area. The economics of the project have proven to be sound, based on the sale of both thermal energy as well as electrical power. The Pre-Feasibility Study Report is included in this response.\r\n\r\nConclusion of the Bankable Feasibility Study is scheduled for November 2013.\r\nFinancial Close is scheduled for June 2014.\r\nConstruction is scheduled to take 18 months.\r\nCommercial Operation is scheduled for Q1 2016.\r\n\r\nThe project is in the early phase of the development cycle and has been submitted in terms of this RFRI to inform the DoE of the prospective power that is intended to be made available in the Rosslyn area.\r\n\r\n', 'Reciprocating', 'Gas', 'ExistingGas', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '32', '2.7', '25', '90', '1.35', 'CPI + gas passthrough', '44%', '', '', '', 'Quater1', '2016', '', '18', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '510', '20', '120', 'The tariff price will be linked to the Liquid natural gas price in terms of the supply contract with Sasol.', 'CPI + gas price pass through', 'yes', '', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', '', '2', '18', 'BR Energy Ubu Investement Holdings JV', 'GE Jenbacher or Wartsilla', 'BR Energy', 'None', 'Basil Read Energy (Pty) Ltd (“BRE”) is a 100% South African owned, energy company. The company is wholly-owned by