(166, 276, 'HyGen Group (Pty) Ltd', '+27826818016', 'Shane Verster', 'N/A', '48', 'Wimbledon Way', 'Edgemead', 'Cape Town', '7441', 'shaneverster@hygengroup.co.za', 'Fish River Community Project - Baroda POC', 'Overview\r\nElectrical supply and stability within the Cradock region is inconsistent. Along the Great Brak and Great Fish rivers, there are several points where small scale hydroelectric units can be installed.\r\nThis project requires the installation of generation equipment to an existing weir located on the Great Fish River approximately 14Km downstream from the Grassridge Dam, in the Eastern Cape. Water supply from the Great Brak River will be passed through the machines to generate power to the grid. The existing weir will create a hydraulic head allowing the generation of renewable electrical power.\r\nAt the site, all relevant control and protection gear will be supplied ensuring that current legislation and standards are met.\r\nThe electrical power will be distributed to the grid via a POC (Point of Coupling) to the utility. The POC will be located approximately 2Km from the site and will be located adjacent to an Eskom supply. At this point the power, via the turbines and the distribution system, will be controlled and metered. The Eskom Interconnection Standard has been adopted within the design and feasibility study.\r\nThe turbine component will be sourced from abroad. All further related equipment and materials will be sourced locally and will be outsourced to local consultants and contractors to design, procure and contract manage (EPCM).\r\nHyGen group will then operate and maintain the machinery for the duration of the PPA based on our knowledge relating to hydroelectric power and managing a PPA with a Utility.\r\nIt is envisaged that the sites will generate the following electrical power and energy per annum through the POC to the utility:\r\n•	Site A:	0.9MW and 1.614GWh per annum\r\n\r\nFuel Supply (arrangements)\r\nThe “fuel” source will be water which is supplied from the Grassridge dam. This supply is consistently supplied throughout the year except within June when, between ten (10) to twenty (20) days of the year, there is a river shut to perform annual maintenance. Water will not be “used” during the process as is the case for irrigation. Instead, the potential energy within the water source transferred to electrical energy through the turbines and then discharged back into the river in order to harness the power.\r\n\r\nMain cost drivers for project.\r\nSite A\r\n1.	Civils – R2M\r\n2.	Turbine and ancillaries – R9M\r\n3.	Electrical distribution, protection and control – R3.4M\r\nPOC\r\n1.	Civils – R0.5M\r\n2.	Electrical distribution, protection and control – R1M\r\nProfessional Fees\r\n1.	Principle Consultant and Project Management– R1.2M\r\n2.	Civils and Mechanical- R1.4M\r\n3.	Electrical and Instrumentation- R0.6M\r\nTotal Project Cost R19.1M\r\n\r\nDecision points to proceed. (Please refer to attached Gantt for more detail)\r\n1.	Application as a preferred bidder with the DoE.\r\n2.	Application for a generation licence with NERSA.\r\n3.	Application to DWA for water licence.\r\n4.	Application to Eskom to connect to Grid.\r\n5.	Securing a PPA.\r\n6.	Approval of funding from financiers.\r\n7.	Appointment of Principle contractor to project.\r\n8.	Design and procurement of Equipment.\r\n9.	Construction and Installation completion.\r\n10.	Commissioning.\r\n11.	COD.\r\n\r\nUnusual features\r\nAll items, except the electrical overhead lines, within this project will be positioned so as to limit the aesthetic layout of the land. \r\nTiming of weir, forebay and tailrace development is critical as the river is shut once a year during June for between 20 to 30 days. During this time all works related to civil works adjacent or on the river will need to take place. That would include any temporary break waters or diverting.\r\n', 'Hydro', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1.1', '1.1', '1', '80', '0.85', '0', '', '', '0', '', 'Quater4', '2015', '', '24', 'none', '11', '30', '24', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '19.1', '15', '880', '', 'None', 'yes', '', 'fastQ3-2013-36Month', '', '3', '26', 'HyGen Group (Pty) Ltd', 'Turbine and components short listed to three suppliers from Germany, India and China.', 'None', 'None', 'We are a new company and the experience has been within working environments outside of the business. The designer has been part of the design team for a new 25MW steam turbine for past employment in Swaziland and also designed, procured, project managed, commissioned and managed the installation of a 1.5MW hydroelectric system in Swaziland.\r\nWithin the team we have experience in running a 43MW (combined) steam and hydroelectric “generator” managing the PPA with SEC in Swaziland.\r\n', '0', '0', '0', 'no', '', '', '', '', 30, 'Houses used to facilitate the construction work force will be reused to on the farmlands and within the community once the project has been completed. Local contractors and workforce will be used as far as reasonably practicable to construct and supply materials for the project.', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '3', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', 'DWA have been contacted to initiate approvals for water usage licence', 'no', 'EIA site visit to date only', 'no', 'Once PPA and funding in place civil works will transpire', 'Immediate', 'See Gantt Chart', 'See Gantt Chart', '4', 'project', '', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '', '', '', '3', 'no', 'draft', 'no', 'Most have been completed but need to be verified by a third party. CSIR have been approached to do so.', 'Cradock, Eastern Cape, South Africa', '31', '57', '18.64', '25', '31', '35.72', 'yes', 'Land Owners have agreed in principle', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'DWA for water usage\r\nNersa for generation licence\r\nZoning Application\r\n', '3', '31', '56', '14.25', '25', '32', '02.88', 'Unknown', 'no', '', '', '', 'Have had contact with Regional Engineer to establish routes and POC point in the region.', 'No transmission line, however, the protection on the line will need to be upgraded.', 'Eskom', '8', 'None', '40-45', '10.1', '52.88', 'Civil works, Housing, Electrical Infrastructure and Design', '50', 'BBEEE in house Engineer in Training and maintenance development within the region.', '2013-07-11', '2013-07-11', 'true');
