(174, 235, 'A D I INVESTMENT (PTY) LTD', '012 348 6350', '012 348 6350', 'LYNNWOOD GLEN ESTATE', '73', 'ELVERAM', 'LYNNWOOD', 'PRETORIA', '0081', 'admin@adiengineers.com', 'REQUEST FOR REGISTRATION AND INFORMATION ISSUED TO POTENTIAL DEVELOPERS OF NEW GENERATION CAPACITY: MEDIUM TERM RISK MITIGATION ( INCLUDING COGENERATION AND NATURAL GAS); AND BASELOAD (INCLUDING COAL, NATURAL GAS AND HYDRO)', '\r\n\r\nIn response to the Determination to deal with Medium Term Risk Mitigation energy and Baseload energy by the Department of Energy of South Africa. The alternative fuel source that is feasible and will be able to meet the DoE’s objectives is biomass. There is much potential in biomass derived energy in meeting South Africa’s energy needs especially electricity. Biomass energy can be obtained from sugarcane, starch, trees such as eucalyptus and palm oil all which can be grown in the country. Bagasse can also be used to produce energy for fuel. The energy forms that can be produced by various forms of biomass can be used to heat thermal power stations to generate electricity. \r\n\r\nHowever, there are critical issues that need to be addressed in exploiting plant based energy: such biomass as sugarcane, corn, etc are food crops and therefore there be a problem of energy needs competing with food production requirements. There will completion for land that can be used to grow food crops and feed the population, the completion for the crops themselves for food use and for energy use. This problem can be averted by reliance on waste residues of sugarcane for instance bagasse. There are large sugar plantations in the country that grow sugarcane. The bagasse as by product of sugarcane processing into sugar can be utilised to produce bio-fuels that can then be used in thermal power station to produce the required heat. \r\n\r\nThere is a great advantage for the shit by the country into biomass derived energy. Firstly the country is producing much of its energy from coal, and coal produce a lot of carbon dioxide, a greenhouse gas. This gas is undesirable and collective efforts are being made the world to curb the transmissions of greenhouse gases so as to avert catastrophic climatic changes. Meeting these requirements is a moral obligation of every nation, so that South Africa will be on the right path of economic development if it meets these goals. The other aspect that make it very crucial for the country to use other forms of renewable energy.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2013-07-11', '0000-00-00', '');
