(209, 186, 'Worcester Gasification Project', '0861004637', 'Johannes Wolmarans', 'Solek & Bathrooms4U', '15', 'George Blake', 'Plankenburg', 'Stellenbosch', '7599', 'johannes@solek.co.za', 'Worcester Gasification Project', 'The project involves a typical gasification facility as currently under development by Solek (Renewable Energy Engineers). The client in this specific case runs a chicken hatchery, while adjacent chicken farms are envisioned to supply waste to the gasification facility. The potential for power generation and waste management are the main drivers behind the project. Project feasibility is mainly based on income earned from energy sold by off-setting the hatchery''s own consumption as well as selling electricity under bilateral trading agreements (willing buyer, wililng seller). Furthermore, aims are to assist in the development of domestic renewable energy technology and skills and promote a low-carbon energy industry. The process involves the supply of animal manure to a gasification facility which in turn produces Syngas (hydrogen and carbon monoxide) for combustion in a power generating engine.', 'Reciprocating', 'Gas', 'other33', '', '', '', '', '', 'Syngas/wood-flue gas (mainly composed of hydrogen and carbon monoxide)', '', '', '', '1.5', '1.5', '1.5', '95', '1.00', 'CPI increase', '', '', '', '', 'Quater4', '2015', 'Construction period is 2-3 months, main time constraint is manufacturing lead times of equipment.', '12', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'yes', '500kVA baseload', '75', '15', '1000', '', 'n/a', 'yes', '', 'commitQ2-2014-Phased', 'commit Q2-2014 - Phased', '8', '18', 'Solek', 'NECSA - Nuclear Energy Corporation of South Africa', 'n/a', 'n/a', 'NECSA has about 20 years development experience in gasification. ', '5000000', '5000000', '5000000', 'no', '', '', '', '', 5, 'Indirect job creation.', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'no', '3', 'yes', 'no', 'yes', '02/12/2013', 'no', '01/09/2013', 'yes', '', '', '', '', 