y the Umfolozi Sugar Mill (Pty) Ltd', 'no', 'no', '', 'no', '', '', 'no', '', '', 'Nersa tariff, Eskom PPA, EIA, Permission to operate high pressure boiler', '0.5', '32', '10', '54.2', '28', '26', '36.8', 'Mtuba Depot sub-station', 'no', '', '', '', 'Initial phase completed in November 2012 and currently exporting 4 MW', 'No upgrade required for Phase 1 or Phase 2 (up to 10 MW export) but an upgrade is required for Phase 3 (20 MW export).', 'ESKOM', '0', 'N/A', '55-65', '450', '75.00', 'Boilers, structural steel work, civil construction, electrical installations, etc.', '400', 'Sugar Training Centre to train boiler operators, electrical components (eg panels and cable racks), instrumentation panels and associated racking, various boiler components (eg tubes, air heaters, grates, chains, panels, cladding/insulation, fans, stacks, conveyor systems, etc)', '2013-07-15', '2013-07-15', ''),
(222, 410, 'Xstrata South Africa (Pty) Ltd', '+27 83 251 9138', 'Mike Rossouw', '3rd Floor, Melrose Arch', '23', 'Melrose Boulevard', 'Melrose Arch', 'Johannesburg', '2196', 'mrossouw@xstrata.co.za', 'Project Lesedi', 'Xstrata South Africa (Pty) Ltd, a member of the Glencore group of companies is sole sponsor for project Lesedi ("Lesedi"). Lesedi refers to the development of a 2x150MW Circulating Fluidised Bed Combustion Coal-Fired Power Plant located at the Xstrata South Africa ("XSA") Tweefontein Colliery within the Mpumalanga Province of South Africa.\r\n \r\nThe Power Plant is planned to operate as a base load plant with the benefit of a long-term Power Purchase Agreement and a commercial operation date planned for 2017. The fuel will be blended coal produced from low grade and discard coal sourced from Xstrata Coal (a division of XSA), respectively and located adjacent to the site of the power plant. \r\n\r\nProject Lesedi has been developed to a relatively advanced stage with a number of the key permits and license in place as well as heads of terms for the fuel supply agreement.\r\n\r\nAlloys Power Generation SPV, is a special purpose vehicle which has been set up to hold all the rights to Lesedi. Currently, Xstrata South Africa is the sole shareholder of Alloys Power Generation. \r\n\r\nThe proposed Power Plant will be constructed on a turnkey basis on a site adjacent to the existing Tweefontein Colliery owned by XSA.  The site is located approximately 22km south-west of Witbank.  The Power Plant site will be located near the coal washing facilities of the XSA Coal mine.  This is a fairly flat terrain area with an elevation of approximately 1,600 m above sea level.  \r\n\r\nThe Power Plant will be fuelled by the coal supplied by XSA from its Tweefontein Colliery.  The coal will be delivered by an overland conveyor belt directly from the blending plant to the Power Plant site.  The overland conveyor will also include a belt scale and sampling system to confirm the weights and coal quality delivered by the colliery.  The infrastructure facilities of the Project will include provisions for receiving and storing of these fuels for use by the Power Plant.  \r\n\r\nRaw water for the Project will be sourced from the existing XSA Coal mines.  Ground water will be abstracted and pumped into a primary water storage reservoir at the XSA Coal mine.  Raw water will then be piped from the primary storage reservoir at the coal mine to a delivery point at the Power Plant security fence boundary terminating in a flanged pipe joint.  A pipeline stemming from this delivery point will be routed to the Power Plant site to supply the water requirements for the project.  \r\n  \r\nEmissions resulting from the combustion of coal will be controlled to comply with either the World Bank or South African emissions limits, whichever is more stringent.  The sulphur dioxide emission will comply with the emissions limits of the DEA.  SO2 emission from the Power Plant will be controlled by means of limestone injection in the combustion zone of the CFB steam generators (boilers).  Limestone will be delivered to the Power Plant by trucks.  Particulate matter emission will be controlled by means of pulse jet fabric filter.  A common stack or chimney with two flues (one flue for each unit) will be provided for the discharge of combustion gases into the atmosphere to meet air quality limitations and regulations associated with dispersion of pollutants and to meet ground level concentrations.  The Power Plant will be designed as a zero liquid effluent discharge facility.  The project received environmental approval from the Department of Environmental Affairs as well as an Atmospheric Emission Licence. The outstanding licenses include the Integrated Water Use Licence and Generation Licencing.   \r\n \r\nPower generated from the Power Plant will be evacuated via Eskom’s 132kV Grootpan substation which a budget quote was received from Eskom in 2012.  Eskom has also received the environmental approval for the distribution infrastructure for the connection.  \r\n', 'Thermal', 'Coal', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '300', '150', '274', '85', '0.91', 'CPI', '95', '', '', '', 'Quater2', '2017', 'COD will be depended on PPA terms and local content requirements.  The first unit of 150MW will be 39 months, there after the second unit in 42 months', '39', 'baseload', '', '', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', 'no', '', '7950', '20', '910', '', 'CPI', 'yes', '', 'commitQ3-2013-Phased', '', '6', '39', 'Xstrata South Africa (Pty) Ltd', 'To be Confirmed', 'To be Confirmed', 'To be Confirmed', 'Xstrata South Africa have developed project Lesedi internally and will be selecting an experienced international partner for the project.  This process will be dependent on the PPA negotiation or procurement process.', '0', '0', '0', 'yes', '', '', '', '', 26, 'Community involvement and local economic development of this area will be included in the already extensive corporate social investment by Xstrata South Africa and more specific to the project include;\r\n\r\n1. Significant job creation during construction activities\r\n2. A carbon emission reduction program was launched by Xstrata South Africa for the implementation of clean burning coal methods in the local community and thus project will be driven by the project.\r\n3. Local construction activities will be included in the project spend  ', 'yes', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '6', 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', '01/02/2017', 'no', '', 'yes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '6', 'project', '', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '6', '', 'finalised', 'yes', 'All studies have been completed', 'Ogies, Mpumalanga, South Africa', '29', '6', '41.96', '26', '2', '48.31', 'yes', 'Xstrata South Africa is the owner of the proposed site and depending on the final project structure the site will either be leased by the Special Purpose Vehicle (SPV) or owned.  The SPV will require consent from the Department of Agriculture for the long term lease, which has been applied for and are awaiting outcome.  ', 'yes', 'yes', '', 'yes', '01/02/2012', '30/11/2013', 'no', '', '', 'The following permits and Licences have been applied for and are awaiting approval;1. Integrated Water Use License - awaiting approval for the last 18 months.  2. Generation License - awaiting approval for the last 12 months', '2.8', '29', '5', '28.24', '26', '2', '41.46', 'Grootpan Distribution Substation', 'yes', '01/10/2009', 'yes', 'Eskom Budget Quote Ref no. KNOTN304', 'Project received and accepted the Eskom budget quote and Eskom completed the environmental process for the proposed connection in 2012', 'A 132kV distribution line will have to built for the project, please refer to the Eskom budget quote ref no. KNOTN304 for details.', 'Eskom', '18', 'Project located in South Africa', '65-75', '2000', '25.16', 'Local civil and steel construction companies will be utilized during the construction phase of the project. Manufacturing of balance of plant equipment such as fans, pumps, valves , ect will be included in the project spend ', '2500', 'Opportunities exist for local component manufacturers for the balance of plant equipment such as fans and pumps, ect.  During the operational phase of the power plant there will be a need for maintenance of the units and there exist opportunities for local maintenance service providers.  ', '2013-07-15', '2013-07-15', ''),
